 to figma\",\n    \"figma daemon\",\n    \"figma mcp\"\n  ],\n  \"derived\": {\n    \"trigger_phrases\": [\n      \"figma cli\",\n      \"figma-ds-cli\",\n      \"figma desktop\",\n      \"render in figma\",\n      \"figma tokens\",\n      \"extract design.md\",\n      \"connect to figma\",\n      \"figma mcp\"\n    ],\n    \"key_topics\": [\n      \"figma-ds-cli binary (and the unrelated figma-cli npm collision)\",\n      \"Figma Desktop session + local daemon (HTTP 127.0.0.1:3456)\",\n      \"safe (plugin) vs yolo (app.asar patch) connect modes\",\n      \"read-only / mutating / destructive command gating\",\n      \"design-system extract (DESIGN.md) and import (tailwind/css/tokens/storybook)\",\n      \"tokens, variables, var:name binding\",\n      \"optional Framelink figma MCP via Code Mode\",\n      \"sk-interface-design handoff for design judgment\"\n    ],\n    \"intent_signals\": [\n      \"figma\",\n      \"figma-ds-cli\",\n      \"figma desktop\",\n      \"design tokens\",\n      \"figma export\",\n      \"figma mcp\",\n      \"code mode figma\"\n    ],\n    \"key_files\": [\n      \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/SKILL.md\",\n      \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/README.md\",\n      \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/INSTALL_GUIDE.md\",\n      \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/references/figma_cli_reference.md\",\n      \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/references/tool_surface.md\",\n      \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/references/mcp_wiring.md\",\n      \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/references/troubleshooting.md\",\n      \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/feature_catalog/feature_catalog.md\",\n      \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md\",\n      \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/changelog/v0.1.0.0.md\"\n    ],\n    \"entities\": [\n      {\"name\": \"mcp-figma\", \"kind\": \"skill\", \"path\": \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/SKILL.md\", \"source\": \"derived\"},\n      {\"name\": \"README\", \"kind\": \"reference\", \"path\": \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/README.md\", \"source\": \"derived\"},\n      {\"name\": \"figma_cli_reference\", \"kind\": \"reference\", \"path\": \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/references/figma_cli_reference.md\", \"source\": \"derived\"},\n      {\"name\": \"tool_surface\", \"kind\": \"reference\", \"path\": \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/references/tool_surface.md\", \"source\": \"derived\"},\n      {\"name\": \"mcp_wiring\", \"kind\": \"reference\", \"path\": \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/references/mcp_wiring.md\", \"source\": \"derived\"},\n      {\"name\": \"troubleshooting\", \"kind\": \"reference\", \"path\": \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/references/troubleshooting.md\", \"source\": \"derived\"}\n    ],\n    \"causal_summary\": \"mcp-figma teaches a terminal agent to drive Figma Desktop through the silships figma-cli, published to npm as figma-ds-cli (the npm package literally named figma-cli is an unrelated tool by unic, bin 'figma' - never install it). figma-cli has no MCP of its own; it drives the live Figma Desktop session via a local daemon (HTTP 127.0.0.1:3456, X-Daemon-Token). Connect is either safe (FigCli plugin, no patch - the default) or yolo (patches Figma app.asar, CDP 9222 - gated, rollback via unpatch). The CLI is primary for authoring/modifying/exporting in Figma; an optional Figma MCP (the community Framelink figma manual already in this repo's Code Mode) is opt-in for pulling design data into the agent for codegen. Commands are gated read-only / mutating / destructive, with eval/raw/run treated as arbitrary mutation and local exports requiring explicit no-overwrite paths. Pairs with sk-interface-design (design judgment) and sk-code (adapting exports into an app). Modeled on mcp-chrome-devtools and mcp-open-design.\",\n    \"source_docs\": [\n      \"SKILL.md\",\n      \"README.md\",\n      \"INSTALL_GUIDE.md\",\n      \"references/figma_cli_reference.md\",\n      \"references/tool_surface.md\",\n      \"references/mcp_wiring.md\",\n      \"references/troubleshooting.md\",\n      \"feature_catalog/feature_catalog.md\",\n      \"manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md\",\n      \"changelog/v0.1.0.0.md\"\n    ],\n    \"created_at\": \"2026-06-14T16:00:00Z\",\n    \"last_updated_at\": \"2026-06-14T16:00:00Z\"\n  }\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":125,"totalLines":125,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/graph-metadata.json","time":{"start":1781459253895,"end":1781459253899}},"id":"prt_ec73efa84001Iz6gR7udn1Lo1U","sessionID":"ses_138c2bb01ffeUjkBZZt6lKZbis","messageID":"msg_ec73eecf1001M64MZwQAoNqVRp"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781459254429,"sessionID":"ses_138c2bb01ffeUjkBZZt6lKZbis","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_3bf98835b06d44938fa32c06","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/mcp-figma/references/troubleshooting.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/mcp-figma/references/troubleshooting.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Figma CLI Troubleshooting\"\n3: description: \"Symptom to cause to fix guide for common figma-ds-cli, daemon, connect, and optional Code Mode MCP issues.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"figma-cli command not found\"\n6:   - \"figma-ds-cli troubleshooting\"\n7:   - \"figma daemon unauthorized\"\n8:   - \"figma connect safe mode\"\n9:   - \"figma yolo patch broke\"\n10:   - \"figma code mode variable not found\"\n11: importance_tier: \"normal\"\n12: contextType: \"implementation\"\n13: ---\n14: \n15: # Figma CLI Troubleshooting\n16: \n17: > **IMPORTANT:** Examples in this guide are illustrative. The CLI is not assumed to be installed in any given environment, so command output is not reproduced literally — verify the actual surface with `figma-ds-cli --help` (or the relevant subcommand's `--help`) before relying on a flag or verb.\n18: \n19: ---\n20: \n21: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n22: \n23: ### Core Principle\n24: \n25: Find the root cause before applying a fix — symptom fixes create cascading failures. The most common traps are upstream of any Figma operation: the wrong package installed under a colliding name, an old Node, Figma Desktop not open, or a connect mode that was never completed. Work the quick diagnostics first, then jump to the matching symptom row.\n26: \n27: ### When to Use\n28: \n29: - Diagnose a `figma-ds-cli` install, binary-collision, connect, daemon, or port-conflict failure before mutating anything.\n30: - Resolve an optional Figma MCP (Code Mode) discovery or env-prefix failure.\n31: \n32: ### Key Sources\n33: \n34: - [figma_cli_reference.md](figma_cli_reference.md) - binary identity, connect modes, and the daemon model behind these symptoms.\n35: - [tool_surface.md](tool_surface.md) - the command gating classes the escalation rows reference.\n36: - [mcp_wiring.md](mcp_wiring.md) - the optional Code Mode MCP path and its `.env` prefix.\n37: \n38: Two hard facts shape every fix below:\n39: \n40: - **The canonical binary is `figma-ds-cli`** (silships, npm, MIT). The npm package literally named `figma-cli` is an **unrelated** tool (unic/figma-cli, bin `figma`). The `figma-cli` command only exists when installed from the silships git repo. **Never `npm i -g figma-cli`.**\n41: - **The CLI drives the live Figma Desktop session** — Figma Desktop must be **open with a file**, Node must be **>=18**, and there is **no Figma API key** for the CLI. macOS is the supported baseline; Linux/Windows are experimental and unverified.\n42: \n43: ---\n44: \n45: ## 2. PREREQUISITES\n46: \n47: Before deeper troubleshooting, confirm the foundation:\n48: \n49: - **5-Check Sequence**: Binary identity -> Node version -> Figma Desktop open -> Connect mode completed -> Daemon health.\n50: - **Platform Awareness**: macOS is the supported baseline. Linux/Windows are experimental and unverified — treat platform-specific failures there as unsupported.\n51: - **Error Capture**: Use `2>&1` so stderr is visible when a command appears to do nothing.\n52: \n53: **Required knowledge**:\n54: \n55: - Basic Bash/terminal usage.\n56: - npm global install and PATH concepts.\n57: - The difference between the safe plugin connect and the gated yolo patch (see `figma_cli_reference.md`).\n58: \n59: ---\n60: \n61: ## 3. QUICK DIAGNOSTICS\n62: \n63: Run these checks first. All examples are illustrative — confirm with `--help`.\n64: \n65: ```bash\n66: # 1. Which Figma binary is on PATH? (canonical = figma-ds-cli)\n67: command -v figma-ds-cli || echo \"figma-ds-cli not found\"\n68: command -v figma-cli    || echo \"figma-cli not present (this is fine; figma-ds-cli is canonical)\"\n69: \n70: # 2. Node version (must be >=18)\n71: node --version\n72: \n73: # 3. Is Figma Desktop installed? (must also be OPEN with a file)\n74: ls -d /Applications/Figma.app 2>/dev/null || echo \"Figma Desktop not found in /Applications\"\n75: \n76: # 4. Daemon health (only meaningful after a connect)\n77: figma-ds-cli daemon status 2>&1\n78: # If unhealthy:\n79: figma-ds-cli daemon diagnose 2>&1\n80: \n81: # 5. Daemon endpoint / token presence (do NOT print the token contents)\n82: ls -l ~/.figma-ds-cli/.daemon-token 2>/dev/null || echo \"no daemon token yet\"\n83: ```\n84: \n85: ---\n86: \n87: ## 4. INSTALLATION ISSUES\n88: \n89: ### Issue: `figma-ds-cli: command not found`\n90: \n91: **Symptoms**:\n92: \n93: ```bash\n94: $ figma-ds-cli --version\n95: bash: figma-ds-cli: command not found\n96: ```\n97: \n98: **Diagnosis**:\n99: \n100: ```bash\n101: # Was anything installed under the silships name?\n102: npm list -g figma-ds-cli 2>&1\n103: \n104: # Is the npm global bin directory on PATH?\n105: npm config get prefix\n106: echo \"$PATH\"\n107: ```\n108: \n109: **Causes**:\n110: \n111: - `figma-ds-cli` was never installed.\n112: - It was installed but the npm global bin directory is not on `PATH`.\n113: \n114: **Fix**:\n115: \n116: 1. **Install the correct package** (npm-published; canonical binary):\n117:    ```bash\n118:    npm i -g figma-ds-cli      # illustrative; verifies as figma-ds-cli\n119:    ```\n120:    The newer repo build (which also exposes a `figma-cli` alias) installs from the silships git repo instead:\n121:    ```bash\n122:    npm i -g git+https://github.com/silships/figma-cli.git\n123:    # or: clone OUTSIDE this repo, then npm link\n124:    ```\n125: 2. **Fix PATH** if the binary exists but is not found — add the npm global bin to your shell profile and re-source it.\n126: 3. **Never** `npm i -g figma-cli` to recover — that pulls the unrelated tool (see next row).\n127: \n128: ---\n129: \n130: ### Issue: accidentally installed the unrelated npm `figma-cli`\n131: \n132: **Symptoms**:\n133: \n134: ```bash\n135: # `figma` exists but none of the figma-ds-cli verbs work:\n136: $ figma connect --safe\n137: # unknown command / unrelated help text (this is unic/figma-cli, not silships)\n138: ```\n139: \n140: **Cause**: `npm i -g figma-cli` installs **`figma-cli` v1.0.0 by \"Fredi Bach, Unic AG\"** (repo `unic/figma-cli`, bin `figma`, a Figma-export/scaffold tool for style guides). This is **NOT** the silships tool and shares no command surface with `figma-ds-cli`.\n141: \n142: **Fix**:\n143: \n144: ```bash\n145: # Remove the wrong tool\n146: npm uninstall -g figma-cli      # illustrative\n147: \n148: # Install the correct one. Prefer the skill installer, which lands the full 1.2.0 surface:\n149: scripts/install.sh              # auto: npm, then upgrade from repo when npm is stale\n150: figma-ds-cli --version          # confirm it resolves to the silships tool, >= 1.2.0\n151: ```\n152: \n153: > The silships `figma-cli` **command** only exists when installed from the silships git repo. If a `figma-cli` command is on PATH, confirm it resolves to silships (`figma-cli --version`/`--help`) before trusting it, because the unic npm package shadows the name. Prefer `figma-ds-cli` everywhere.\n154: \n155: ---\n156: \n157: ### Issue: figma-ds-cli is installed but `--safe`, `daemon`, or most commands are missing\n158: \n159: **Symptoms**:\n160: \n161: ```bash\n162: $ figma-ds-cli --version\n163: 1.0.0\n164: $ figma-ds-cli connect --safe\n165: # error: unknown option '--safe'\n166: $ figma-ds-cli daemon status\n167: # error: unknown command 'daemon'\n168: ```\n169: \n170: **Cause**: you have the **npm-published `figma-ds-cli@1.0.0`**, a minimal build. npm only ever published `1.0.0` (no `--safe`, no `daemon`, no `extract`/`import`/`a11y`/`slot`, ~12 commands total). The full surface this skill documents is **1.2.0**, which is **unpublished on npm** and exists only in the silships repo.\n171: \n172: **Fix**:\n173: \n174: ```bash\n175: # Upgrade to 1.2.0 from the silships repo:\n176: scripts/install.sh --source repo --force\n177: figma-ds-cli --version          # expect >= 1.2.0\n178: figma-ds-cli connect --help     # should now list --safe\n179: ```\n180: \n181: > `scripts/install.sh --source auto` (the default) does this automatically: it installs from npm, detects the stale `1.0.0`, and upgrades from the repo.\n182: \n183: ---\n184: \n185: ### Issue: only one binary present (`figma-ds-cli` works, `figma-cli` missing)\n186: \n187: **Symptoms**:\n188: \n189: ```bash\n190: $ command -v figma-ds-cli   # → found\n191: $ command -v figma-cli      # → not found\n192: ```\n193: \n194: **Cause**: The **npm-published** package exposes **only `figma-ds-cli`**. The dual-bin form (`figma-ds-cli` + `figma-cli`) exists only in the newer silships **repo** build (`main`), which is not published to npm.\n195: \n196: **Fix**: This is normal and not an error. **Use `figma-ds-cli` as the canonical command** — every verb in this skill works through it. Only install from the silships repo if you specifically need the newer repo build; do not chase the `figma-cli` alias.\n197: \n198: ---\n199: \n200: ### Issue: Node version too old (Node <18)\n201: \n202: **Symptoms**:\n203: \n204: ```bash\n205: $ figma-ds-cli --version\n206: # errors or unexpected behavior on an old Node runtime\n207: ```\n208: \n209: **Diagnosis**:\n210: \n211: ```bash\n212: node --version   # figma-ds-cli requires Node.js >=18\n213: ```\n214: \n215: **Fix**:\n216: \n217: ```bash\n218: # Using nvm (recommended)\n219: nvm install 18\n220: nvm use 18\n221: # Or install/update Node from nodejs.org, then re-run the install.\n222: ```\n223: \n224: ---\n225: \n226: ## 5. FIGMA DESKTOP ISSUES\n227: \n228: ### Issue: Figma Desktop not found\n229: \n230: **Symptoms**: Connect or any CLI operation fails because there is no Figma Desktop to drive.\n231: \n232: **Diagnosis**:\n233: \n234: ```bash\n235: ls -d /Applications/Figma.app 2>/dev/null || ls -d ~/Applications/Figma.app 2>/dev/null \\\n236:   || echo \"Figma Desktop not installed\"\n237: ```\n238: \n239: **Cause**: The CLI drives the **local Figma Desktop session** — there is no API-key/cloud fallback. Without Figma Desktop installed, nothing connects.\n240: \n241: **Fix**: Install Figma Desktop, then return to the connect flow. (macOS is the supported baseline.)\n242: \n243: ---\n244: \n245: ### Issue: Figma Desktop not running / no file open\n246: \n247: **Symptoms**: The binary is present and Figma is installed, but connect or any document command fails to reach a live document.\n248: \n249: **Cause**: figma-ds-cli requires Figma Desktop to be **open with a file** — the daemon bridges to the active Desktop session, not to a cloud document.\n250: \n251: **Fix**: Launch Figma Desktop, open (or create) a file, keep it focused, then re-run `figma-ds-cli connect --safe` and `figma-ds-cli daemon status`.\n252: \n253: ---\n254: \n255: ### Issue: safe-mode plugin not imported / not open\n256: \n257: **Symptoms**: `figma-ds-cli connect --safe` does not establish a working bridge; daemon stays unhealthy.\n258: \n259: **Cause**: Safe mode runs the **FigCli plugin** as the bridge (no app patch). The plugin must be imported once and then kept open every session.\n260: \n261: **Fix**:\n262: \n263: 1. Confirm Figma Desktop is open with a file.\n264: 2. Import the plugin manifest **once**: in Figma, import `plugin/manifest.json` from the figma-ds-cli install.\n265: 3. Open and **keep open** `Plugins -> Development -> FigCli` for the whole session.\n266: 4. Re-run `figma-ds-cli connect --safe`, then `figma-ds-cli daemon status`.\n267: \n268: > Safe connect (`connect --safe`) is the **default and recommended** path — it never patches Figma.\n269: \n270: ---\n271: \n272: ## 6. CONNECT (YOLO PATCH) ISSUES\n273: \n274: > The yolo patch is **gated**: it modifies Figma Desktop `app.asar` (and codesigns on macOS) and is only run on explicit consent with a stated rollback. The rollback for every yolo failure below is `figma-ds-cli unpatch`.\n275: \n276: ### Issue: yolo patch failed (permissions / Full Disk Access)\n277: \n278: **Symptoms**: `figma-ds-cli connect` (yolo) fails while patching the Figma app, codesigning, or restarting Figma.\n279: \n280: **Cause**: The patch writes to the Figma application bundle and re-signs it. On macOS this can require **Full Disk Access** and/or admin rights; the operation also restarts Figma.\n281: \n282: **Fix**:\n283: \n284: 1. Prefer the safe path instead: `figma-ds-cli connect --safe` (no patch, no special permissions).\n285: 2. If yolo is genuinely required, grant the terminal Full Disk Access (and admin where needed), ensure Figma is safe to restart, re-confirm consent, then re-run `figma-ds-cli connect`.\n286: 3. If the bundle is left in a bad state, revert with `figma-ds-cli unpatch`.\n287: \n288: ---\n289: \n290: ### Issue: yolo connection broke after a Figma update\n291: \n292: **Symptoms**: A previously working yolo connection stops working after Figma Desktop auto-updates.\n293: \n294: **Cause**: A Figma update replaces the patched `app.asar`, undoing the patch (and may invalidate the codesign).\n295: \n296: **Fix**:\n297: \n298: ```bash\n299: # Revert to a known-clean bundle first, then re-establish the connection.\n300: figma-ds-cli unpatch        # illustrative; restore the original app.asar\n301: figma-ds-cli connect --safe # prefer the no-patch path going forward\n302: # (re-run yolo `connect` only on renewed explicit consent)\n303: ```\n304: \n305: ---\n306: \n307: ## 7. DAEMON ISSUES\n308: \n309: The daemon is a local **HTTP server on `127.0.0.1:3456`** (not a Unix socket), authed via the `X-Daemon-Token` header (`~/.figma-ds-cli/.daemon-token`), PID at `~/.figma-cli-daemon.pid`, with an idle timeout (~60 min) and no reboot persistence. Recovery order is always **status -> diagnose -> restart -> reconnect**.\n310: \n311: ### Issue: daemon \"Unauthorized\"\n312: \n313: **Symptoms**:\n314: \n315: ```bash\n316: $ figma-ds-cli daemon status\n317: Unauthorized\n318: ```\n319: \n320: **Cause**: Token mismatch between the client and the running daemon (`X-Daemon-Token`).\n321: \n322: **Fix**:\n323: \n324: ```bash\n325: figma-ds-cli daemon diagnose 2>&1   # inspect the mismatch first\n326: figma-ds-cli daemon restart 2>&1    # restart re-aligns the token\n327: ```\n328: \n329: > **Never auto-delete the token** (`~/.figma-ds-cli/.daemon-token`) and never print its contents in user-facing output. Diagnose, then restart — deletion is not the remedy.\n330: \n331: ---\n332: \n333: ### Issue: daemon unreachable on port 3456\n334: \n335: **Symptoms**: Daemon-backed commands hang or fail to connect to `127.0.0.1:3456`.\n336: \n337: **Diagnosis**:\n338: \n339: ```bash\n340: figma-ds-cli daemon status 2>&1\n341: ls -l ~/.figma-cli-daemon.pid 2>/dev/null   # is a daemon recorded?\n342: lsof -nP -iTCP:3456 -sTCP:LISTEN 2>/dev/null # who, if anyone, owns 3456\n343: ```\n344: \n345: **Causes**:\n346: \n347: - The daemon idled out (~60 min) — it is not reboot-persistent.\n348: - The daemon crashed.\n349: - Another process holds port 3456.\n350: \n351: **Fix**:\n352: \n353: 1. **Idle / crashed**: `figma-ds-cli daemon restart` (then `daemon reconnect` if the bridge is up but the document link dropped).\n354: 2. **Port owned by another process**: identify the owner with `lsof` first — **never blind-kill** the port. If it is a stale figma-ds-cli daemon, `daemon restart`; otherwise resolve the owning process before reusing 3456.\n355: \n356: ---\n357: \n358: ## 8. PORT CONFLICT ISSUES\n359: \n360: ### Issue: port 9222 conflict (yolo / CDP)\n361: \n362: **Symptoms**: A yolo connection fails to expose CDP, or another tool is already using port 9222.\n363: \n364: **Cause**: The yolo patch restarts Figma with remote debugging on **fixed CDP port 9222**. Another Chromium-based tool (for example a browser-debugging session) may already hold 9222.\n365: \n366: **Fix**:\n367: \n368: ```bash\n369: lsof -nP -iTCP:9222 -sTCP:LISTEN 2>/dev/null   # identify the owner FIRST\n370: ```\n371: \n372: - If a different tool owns 9222 (for example a `mcp-chrome-devtools` session), stop that tool or free the port, then re-establish the Figma yolo connection.\n373: - Do not kill an unidentified process — confirm the owner before acting.\n374: - Prefer `connect --safe`, which uses the plugin bridge and does not need port 9222.\n375: \n376: ---\n377: \n378: ## 9. OPTIONAL MCP (CODE MODE) ISSUES\n379: \n380: The optional Figma MCP is the community **Framelink `figma-developer-mcp`**, already registered in this repo's Code Mode as the manual **`figma`** (stdio). The CLI works fully without it; the MCP is opt-in and only for pulling design context FROM Figma. The official Figma Dev Mode MCP is **out of scope for this release** — do not document it as a supported path. (A future option only.)\n381: \n382: ### Issue: Code Mode \"variable not found\" for the Figma token\n383: \n384: **Symptoms**: Code Mode cannot resolve the Figma API key for the `figma` manual, even though the config references `${FIGMA_API_KEY}`.\n385: \n386: **Cause**: Code Mode **prefixes each manual's env vars with the manual name**. The `figma` manual therefore needs the key as **`figma_FIGMA_API_KEY`**, not bare `FIGMA_API_KEY`.\n387: \n388: **Fix**:\n389: \n390: ```bash\n391: # In .env (illustrative — do not paste the token into chat output):\n392: figma_FIGMA_API_KEY=figd_your_token_here\n393: ```\n394: \n395: Set `figma_FIGMA_API_KEY` in `.env`, then restart Code Mode so the manual reloads. Never expose the token in user-facing output.\n396: \n397: ---\n398: \n399: ### Issue: Framelink `figma` tools missing in Code Mode\n400: \n401: **Symptoms**: `call_tool_chain()` cannot find any `figma.figma_<tool>` to call.\n402: \n403: **Diagnosis / Fix** (discover first, never guess names):\n404: \n405: 1. Confirm the `figma` manual is registered in `.utcp_config.json` (`manual_call_templates`), stdio, `npx -y figma-developer-mcp@latest --stdio`.\n406: 2. Ensure `figma_FIGMA_API_KEY` is set in `.env` (see the row above).\n407: 3. **Restart Code Mode** so the manual loads.\n408: 4. Discover the real surface before invoking:\n409:    ```text\n410:    list_tools()        # filter by the \"figma\" prefix\n411:    search_tools(...)   # find a tool by intent\n412:    tool_info(...)      # confirm the exact name + params\n413:    ```\n414: 5. Call with the prefixed naming `figma.figma_<tool>`. Do not claim a tool works until discovery confirms it.\n415: \n416: ---\n417: \n418: ## 10. ERROR / SYMPTOM REFERENCE\n419: \n420: | Symptom | Likely cause | Fix |\n421: | --- | --- | --- |\n422: | `figma-ds-cli: command not found` | Not installed, or npm global bin not on PATH | `npm i -g figma-ds-cli`; fix PATH; never `npm i -g figma-cli` |\n423: | `figma` works but figma-ds-cli verbs fail | Installed the unrelated unic/`figma-cli` (bin `figma`) | Uninstall `figma-cli`; install `figma-ds-cli`; verify silships |\n424: | Only `figma-ds-cli` present, no `figma-cli` | npm build ships only `figma-ds-cli`; dual-bin is repo-only | Normal — use `figma-ds-cli` as canonical |\n425: | Errors on old Node | Node <18 | `nvm install 18 && nvm use 18` |\n426: | Figma Desktop not found | Desktop not installed (no cloud fallback) | Install Figma Desktop |\n427: | Connect/doc commands fail | Figma Desktop not running or no file open | Open Figma Desktop with a file, keep it focused |\n428: | `connect --safe` won't bridge | FigCli plugin not imported / not open | Import `plugin/manifest.json` once; keep FigCli open |\n429: | Yolo patch fails | Permissions / Full Disk Access / admin | Grant access or use `--safe`; `unpatch` to revert |\n430: | Yolo broke after Figma update | Update replaced patched `app.asar` | `figma-ds-cli unpatch`, then re-connect (prefer `--safe`) |\n431: | Daemon `Unauthorized` | `X-Daemon-Token` mismatch | `daemon diagnose` then `daemon restart` (never delete token) |\n432: | Daemon unreachable on 3456 | Idle timeout / crash / port owned | `daemon restart`/`reconnect`; identify 3456 owner before reuse |\n433: | CDP port 9222 conflict | Yolo uses fixed 9222; another tool holds it | Identify owner with `lsof`; free it or use `--safe` |\n434: | Code Mode \"variable not found\" | Missing `figma_` env prefix | Set `figma_FIGMA_API_KEY` in `.env`; restart Code Mode |\n435: | `figma` tools missing in Code Mode | Manual not loaded / not discovered | Confirm config + `.env`, restart, `list_tools()`/`tool_info()` |\n436: \n437: ---\n438: \n439: ## 11. COMMON SOLUTIONS CHECKLIST\n440: \n441: Before escalating, confirm:\n442: \n443: - [ ] `figma-ds-cli` is the binary in use (NOT the unrelated unic `figma-cli`).\n444: - [ ] Node is **>=18** (`node --version`).\n445: - [ ] Figma Desktop is **installed, open, and has a file open**.\n446: - [ ] A connect mode completed — safe plugin (default) imported and FigCli kept open, or yolo consented + patched.\n447: - [ ] `daemon status` is healthy (`diagnose` -> `restart` -> `reconnect` if not).\n448: - [ ] The daemon endpoint (`127.0.0.1:3456`) and token file exist; the token was never printed.\n449: - [ ] For Code Mode: `figma_FIGMA_API_KEY` is set in `.env`, Code Mode was restarted, and tools were discovered before calling.\n450: - [ ] No port conflict on 3456 or (yolo) 9222 — owner identified before any kill.\n451: - [ ] Examples were verified against the live `--help` surface, not assumed.\n452: \n453: ---\n454: \n455: ## 12. ESCALATION\n456: \n457: Stop and escalate to the user (with the effect and a one-line rollback) when a quick fix is not safe to choose unilaterally:\n458: \n459: - The binary is **missing or ambiguous** — ask whether to install `figma-ds-cli` (npm) or the silships repo build; do not guess.\n460: - A **yolo patch**, an **unpatch**, or any **destructive verb** is needed to recover — describe the effect and rollback, then wait for confirmation.\n461: - A **port conflict** can only be cleared by stopping an unidentified process — confirm the owner first.\n462: - The **optional Figma MCP** is requested but no token / `figma` manual is configured — surface the `.env` requirement; never paste credentials.\n463: - A failure persists on **Linux/Windows** — those platforms are experimental and unverified; flag the limitation rather than improvising an unsupported fix.\n464: \n465: When reporting a bug upstream, include: the binary in use and version (`figma-ds-cli --version`), Node version, platform (macOS supported), connect mode (safe/yolo), `daemon diagnose` output (token redacted), and the full error with `2>&1`.\n466: \n467: ---\n468: \n469: ## 13. REFERENCES\n470: \n471: - [figma_cli_reference.md](figma_cli_reference.md) - binary identity, Node/macOS baseline, Figma Desktop requirement, connect modes, and the daemon model.\n472: - [tool_surface.md](tool_surface.md) - the read-only / mutating / destructive command taxonomy and the gating rules.\n473: - [mcp_wiring.md](mcp_wiring.md) - the optional Figma MCP (Framelink `figma`) via Code Mode: the registered manual, the `.env` token, and discovery.\n474: - [INSTALL_GUIDE.md](../INSTALL_GUIDE.md) - install steps and binary verification.\n475: - [SKILL.md](../SKILL.md) - the skill contract this reference supports.\n476: - Code Mode transport for the optional MCP: [mcp-code-mode SKILL.md](../../mcp-code-mode/SKILL.md). Browser-debugging owner for port 9222 conflicts: [mcp-chrome-devtools SKILL.md](../../mcp-chrome-devtools/SKILL.md).\n477: - Upstream: [silships/figma-cli](https://github.com/silships/figma-cli) (npm `figma-ds-cli`, MIT). [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/) (>=18). This skill does not vendor either.\n478: \n479: > **Note**: Most failures are upstream of any Figma operation — wrong package under the colliding `figma-cli` name, Node <18, Figma Desktop not open, an incomplete connect mode, or a missing Code Mode env prefix. Verify the binary, Desktop state, and daemon health before deeper diagnosis, and confirm every illustrative command against the live `--help` surface.\n\n(End of file - total 479 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Figma CLI Troubleshooting\"\ndescription: \"Symptom to cause to fix guide for common figma-ds-cli, daemon, connect, and optional Code Mode MCP issues.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"figma-cli command not found\"\n  - \"figma-ds-cli troubleshooting\"\n  - \"figma daemon unauthorized\"\n  - \"figma connect safe mode\"\n  - \"figma yolo patch broke\"\n  - \"figma code mode variable not found\"\nimportance_tier: \"normal\"\ncontextType: \"implementation\"\n---\n\n# Figma CLI Troubleshooting\n\n> **IMPORTANT:** Examples in this guide are illustrative. The CLI is not assumed to be installed in any given environment, so command output is not reproduced literally — verify the actual surface with `figma-ds-cli --help` (or the relevant subcommand's `--help`) before relying on a flag or verb.\n\n---\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/mcp-figma/references/troubleshooting.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"Figma CLI Troubleshooting\"\ndescription: \"Symptom to cause to fix guide for common figma-ds-cli, daemon, connect, and optional Code Mode MCP issues.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"figma-cli command not found\"\n  - \"figma-ds-cli troubleshooting\"\n  - \"figma daemon unauthorized\"\n  - \"figma connect safe mode\"\n  - \"figma yolo patch broke\"\n  - \"figma code mode variable not found\"\nimportance_tier: \"normal\"\ncontextType: \"implementation\"\n---\n\n# Figma CLI Troubleshooting\n\n> **IMPORTANT:** Examples in this guide are illustrative. The CLI is not assumed to be installed in any given environment, so command output is not reproduced literally — verify the actual surface with `figma-ds-cli --help` (or the relevant subcommand's `--help`) before relying on a flag or verb.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Core Principle\n\nFind the root cause before applying a fix — symptom fixes create cascading failures. The most common traps are upstream of any Figma operation: the wrong package installed under a colliding name, an old Node, Figma Desktop not open, or a connect mode that was never completed. Work the quick diagnostics first, then jump to the matching symptom row.\n\n### When to Use\n\n- Diagnose a `figma-ds-cli` install, binary-collision, connect, daemon, or port-conflict failure before mutating anything.\n- Resolve an optional Figma MCP (Code Mode) discovery or env-prefix failure.\n\n### Key Sources\n\n- [figma_cli_reference.md](figma_cli_reference.md) - binary identity, connect modes, and the daemon model behind these symptoms.\n- [tool_surface.md](tool_surface.md) - the command gating classes the escalation rows reference.\n- [mcp_wiring.md](mcp_wiring.md) - the optional Code Mode MCP path and its `.env` prefix.\n\nTwo hard facts shape every fix below:\n\n- **The canonical binary is `figma-ds-cli`** (silships, npm, MIT). The npm package literally named `figma-cli` is an **unrelated** tool (unic/figma-cli, bin `figma`). The `figma-cli` command only exists when installed from the silships git repo. **Never `npm i -g figma-cli`.**\n- **The CLI drives the live Figma Desktop session** — Figma Desktop must be **open with a file**, Node must be **>=18**, and there is **no Figma API key** for the CLI. macOS is the supported baseline; Linux/Windows are experimental and unverified.\n\n---\n\n## 2. PREREQUISITES\n\nBefore deeper troubleshooting, confirm the foundation:\n\n- **5-Check Sequence**: Binary identity -> Node version -> Figma Desktop open -> Connect mode completed -> Daemon health.\n- **Platform Awareness**: macOS is the supported baseline. Linux/Windows are experimental and unverified — treat platform-specific failures there as unsupported.\n- **Error Capture**: Use `2>&1` so stderr is visible when a command appears to do nothing.\n\n**Required knowledge**:\n\n- Basic Bash/terminal usage.\n- npm global install and PATH concepts.\n- The difference between the safe plugin connect and the gated yolo patch (see `figma_cli_reference.md`).\n\n---\n\n## 3. QUICK DIAGNOSTICS\n\nRun these checks first. All examples are illustrative — confirm with `--help`.\n\n```bash\n# 1. Which Figma binary is on PATH? (canonical = figma-ds-cli)\ncommand -v figma-ds-cli || echo \"figma-ds-cli not found\"\ncommand -v figma-cli    || echo \"figma-cli not present (this is fine; figma-ds-cli is canonical)\"\n\n# 2. Node version (must be >=18)\nnode --version\n\n# 3. Is Figma Desktop installed? (must also be OPEN with a file)\nls -d /Applications/Figma.app 2>/dev/null || echo \"Figma Desktop not found in /Applications\"\n\n# 4. Daemon health (only meaningful after a connect)\nfigma-ds-cli daemon status 2>&1\n# If unhealthy:\nfigma-ds-cli daemon diagnose 2>&1\n\n# 5. Daemon endpoint / token presence (do NOT print the token contents)\nls -l ~/.figma-ds-cli/.daemon-token 2>/dev/null || echo \"no daemon token yet\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. INSTALLATION ISSUES\n\n### Issue: `figma-ds-cli: command not found`\n\n**Symptoms**:\n\n```bash\n$ figma-ds-cli --version\nbash: figma-ds-cli: command not found\n```\n\n**Diagnosis**:\n\n```bash\n# Was anything installed under the silships name?\nnpm list -g figma-ds-cli 2>&1\n\n# Is the npm global bin directory on PATH?\nnpm config get prefix\necho \"$PATH\"\n```\n\n**Causes**:\n\n- `figma-ds-cli` was never installed.\n- It was installed but the npm global bin directory is not on `PATH`.\n\n**Fix**:\n\n1. **Install the correct package** (npm-published; canonical binary):\n   ```bash\n   npm i -g figma-ds-cli      # illustrative; verifies as figma-ds-cli\n   ```\n   The newer repo build (which also exposes a `figma-cli` alias) installs from the silships git repo instead:\n   ```bash\n   npm i -g git+https://github.com/silships/figma-cli.git\n   # or: clone OUTSIDE this repo, then npm link\n   ```\n2. **Fix PATH** if the binary exists but is not found — add the npm global bin to your shell profile and re-source it.\n3. **Never** `npm i -g figma-cli` to recover — that pulls the unrelated tool (see next row).\n\n---\n\n### Issue: accidentally installed the unrelated npm `figma-cli`\n\n**Symptoms**:\n\n```bash\n# `figma` exists but none of the figma-ds-cli verbs work:\n$ figma connect --safe\n# unknown command / unrelated help text (this is unic/figma-cli, not silships)\n```\n\n**Cause**: `npm i -g figma-cli` installs **`figma-cli` v1.0.0 by \"Fredi Bach, Unic AG\"** (repo `unic/figma-cli`, bin `figma`, a Figma-export/scaffold tool for style guides). This is **NOT** the silships tool and shares no command surface with `figma-ds-cli`.\n\n**Fix**:\n\n```bash\n# Remove the wrong tool\nnpm uninstall -g figma-cli      # illustrative\n\n# Install the correct one. Prefer the skill installer, which lands the full 1.2.0 surface:\nscripts/install.sh              # auto: npm, then upgrade from repo when npm is stale\nfigma-ds-cli --version          # confirm it resolves to the silships tool, >= 1.2.0\n```\n\n> The silships `figma-cli` **command** only exists when installed from the silships git repo. If a `figma-cli` command is on PATH, confirm it resolves to silships (`figma-cli --version`/`--help`) before trusting it, because the unic npm package shadows the name. Prefer `figma-ds-cli` everywhere.\n\n---\n\n### Issue: figma-ds-cli is installed but `--safe`, `daemon`, or most commands are missing\n\n**Symptoms**:\n\n```bash\n$ figma-ds-cli --version\n1.0.0\n$ figma-ds-cli connect --safe\n# error: unknown option '--safe'\n$ figma-ds-cli daemon status\n# error: unknown command 'daemon'\n```\n\n**Cause**: you have the **npm-published `figma-ds-cli@1.0.0`**, a minimal build. npm only ever published `1.0.0` (no `--safe`, no `daemon`, no `extract`/`import`/`a11y`/`slot`, ~12 commands total). The full surface this skill documents is **1.2.0**, which is **unpublished on npm** and exists only in the silships repo.\n\n**Fix**:\n\n```bash\n# Upgrade to 1.2.0 from the silships repo:\nscripts/install.sh --source repo --force\nfigma-ds-cli --version          # expect >= 1.2.0\nfigma-ds-cli connect --help     # should now list --safe\n```\n\n> `scripts/install.sh --source auto` (the default) does this automatically: it installs from npm, detects the stale `1.0.0`, and upgrades from the repo.\n\n---\n\n### Issue: only one binary present (`figma-ds-cli` works, `figma-cli` missing)\n\n**Symptoms**:\n\n```bash\n$ command -v figma-ds-cli   # → found\n$ command -v figma-cli      # → not found\n```\n\n**Cause**: The **npm-published** package exposes **only `figma-ds-cli`**. The dual-bin form (`figma-ds-cli` + `figma-cli`) exists only in the newer silships **repo** build (`main`), which is not published to npm.\n\n**Fix**: This is normal and not an error. **Use `figma-ds-cli` as the canonical command** — every verb in this skill works through it. Only install from the silships repo if you specifically need the newer repo build; do not chase the `figma-cli` alias.\n\n---\n\n### Issue: Node version too old (Node <18)\n\n**Symptoms**:\n\n```bash\n$ figma-ds-cli --version\n# errors or unexpected behavior on an old Node runtime\n```\n\n**Diagnosis**:\n\n```bash\nnode --version   # figma-ds-cli requires Node.js >=18\n```\n\n**Fix**:\n\n```bash\n# Using nvm (recommended)\nnvm install 18\nnvm use 18\n# Or install/update Node from nodejs.org, then re-run the install.\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. FIGMA DESKTOP ISSUES\n\n### Issue: Figma Desktop not found\n\n**Symptoms**: Connect or any CLI operation fails because there is no Figma Desktop to drive.\n\n**Diagnosis**:\n\n```bash\nls -d /Applications/Figma.app 2>/dev/null || ls -d ~/Applications/Figma.app 2>/dev/null \\\n  || echo \"Figma Desktop not installed\"\n```\n\n**Cause**: The CLI drives the **local Figma Desktop session** — there is no API-key/cloud fallback. Without Figma Desktop installed, nothing connects.\n\n**Fix**: Install Figma Desktop, then return to the connect flow. (macOS is the supported baseline.)\n\n---\n\n### Issue: Figma Desktop not running / no file open\n\n**Symptoms**: The binary is present and Figma is installed, but connect or any document command fails to reach a live document.\n\n**Cause**: figma-ds-cli requires Figma Desktop to be **open with a file** — the daemon bridges to the active Desktop session, not to a cloud document.\n\n**Fix**: Launch Figma Desktop, open (or create) a file, keep it focused, then re-run `figma-ds-cli connect --safe` and `figma-ds-cli daemon status`.\n\n---\n\n### Issue: safe-mode plugin not imported / not open\n\n**Symptoms**: `figma-ds-cli connect --safe` does not establish a working bridge; daemon stays unhealthy.\n\n**Cause**: Safe mode runs the **FigCli plugin** as the bridge (no app patch). The plugin must be imported once and then kept open every session.\n\n**Fix**:\n\n1. Confirm Figma Desktop is open with a file.\n2. Import the plugin manifest **once**: in Figma, import `plugin/manifest.json` from the figma-ds-cli install.\n3. Open and **keep open** `Plugins -> Development -> FigCli` for the whole session.\n4. Re-run `figma-ds-cli connect --safe`, then `figma-ds-cli daemon status`.\n\n> Safe connect (`connect --safe`) is the **default and recommended** path — it never patches Figma.\n\n---\n\n## 6. CONNECT (YOLO PATCH) ISSUES\n\n> The yolo patch is **gated**: it modifies Figma Desktop `app.asar` (and codesigns on macOS) and is only run on explicit consent with a stated rollback. The rollback for every yolo failure below is `figma-ds-cli unpatch`.\n\n### Issue: yolo patch failed (permissions / Full Disk Access)\n\n**Symptoms**: `figma-ds-cli connect` (yolo) fails while patching the Figma app, codesigning, or restarting Figma.\n\n**Cause**: The patch writes to the Figma application bundle and re-signs it. On macOS this can require **Full Disk Access** and/or admin rights; the operation also restarts Figma.\n\n**Fix**:\n\n1. Prefer the safe path instead: `figma-ds-cli connect --safe` (no patch, no special permissions).\n2. If yolo is genuinely required, grant the terminal Full Disk Access (and admin where needed), ensure Figma is safe to restart, re-confirm consent, then re-run `figma-ds-cli connect`.\n3. If the bundle is left in a bad state, revert with `figma-ds-cli unpatch`.\n\n---\n\n### Issue: yolo connection broke after a Figma update\n\n**Symptoms**: A previously working yolo connection stops working after Figma Desktop auto-updates.\n\n**Cause**: A Figma update replaces the patched `app.asar`, undoing the patch (and may invalidate the codesign).\n\n**Fix**:\n\n```bash\n# Revert to a known-clean bundle first, then re-establish the connection.\nfigma-ds-cli unpatch        # illustrative; restore the original app.asar\nfigma-ds-cli connect --safe # prefer the no-patch path going forward\n# (re-run yolo `connect` only on renewed explicit consent)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 7. DAEMON ISSUES\n\nThe daemon is a local **HTTP server on `127.0.0.1:3456`** (not a Unix socket), authed via the `X-Daemon-Token` header (`~/.figma-ds-cli/.daemon-token`), PID at `~/.figma-cli-daemon.pid`, with an idle timeout (~60 min) and no reboot persistence. Recovery order is always **status -> diagnose -> restart -> reconnect**.\n\n### Issue: daemon \"Unauthorized\"\n\n**Symptoms**:\n\n```bash\n$ figma-ds-cli daemon status\nUnauthorized\n```\n\n**Cause**: Token mismatch between the client and the running daemon (`X-Daemon-Token`).\n\n**Fix**:\n\n```bash\nfigma-ds-cli daemon diagnose 2>&1   # inspect the mismatch first\nfigma-ds-cli daemon restart 2>&1    # restart re-aligns the token\n```\n\n> **Never auto-delete the token** (`~/.figma-ds-cli/.daemon-token`) and never print its contents in user-facing output. Diagnose, then restart — deletion is not the remedy.\n\n---\n\n### Issue: daemon unreachable on port 3456\n\n**Symptoms**: Daemon-backed commands hang or fail to connect to `127.0.0.1:3456`.\n\n**Diagnosis**:\n\n```bash\nfigma-ds-cli daemon status 2>&1\nls -l ~/.figma-cli-daemon.pid 2>/dev/null   # is a daemon recorded?\nlsof -nP -iTCP:3456 -sTCP:LISTEN 2>/dev/null # who, if anyone, owns 3456\n```\n\n**Causes**:\n\n- The daemon idled out (~60 min) — it is not reboot-persistent.\n- The daemon crashed.\n- Another process holds port 3456.\n\n**Fix**:\n\n1. **Idle / crashed**: `figma-ds-cli daemon restart` (then `daemon reconnect` if the bridge is up but the document link dropped).\n2. **Port owned by another process**: identify the owner with `lsof` first — **never blind-kill** the port. If it is a stale figma-ds-cli daemon, `daemon restart`; otherwise resolve the owning process before reusing 3456.\n\n---\n\n## 8. PORT CONFLICT ISSUES\n\n### Issue: port 9222 conflict (yolo / CDP)\n\n**Symptoms**: A yolo connection fails to expose CDP, or another tool is already using port 9222.\n\n**Cause**: The yolo patch restarts Figma with remote debugging on **fixed CDP port 9222**. Another Chromium-based tool (for example a browser-debugging session) may already hold 9222.\n\n**Fix**:\n\n```bash\nlsof -nP -iTCP:9222 -sTCP:LISTEN 2>/dev/null   # identify the owner FIRST\n```\n\n- If a different tool owns 9222 (for example a `mcp-chrome-devtools` session), stop that tool or free the port, then re-establish the Figma yolo connection.\n- Do not kill an unidentified process — confirm the owner before acting.\n- Prefer `connect --safe`, which uses the plugin bridge and does not need port 9222.\n\n---\n\n## 9. OPTIONAL MCP (CODE MODE) ISSUES\n\nThe optional Figma MCP is the community **Framelink `figma-developer-mcp`**, already registered in this repo's Code Mode as the manual **`figma`** (stdio). The CLI works fully without it; the MCP is opt-in and only for pulling design context FROM Figma. The official Figma Dev Mode MCP is **out of scope for this release** — do not document it as a supported path. (A future option only.)\n\n### Issue: Code Mode \"variable not found\" for the Figma token\n\n**Symptoms**: Code Mode cannot resolve the Figma API key for the `figma` manual, even though the config references `${FIGMA_API_KEY}`.\n\n**Cause**: Code Mode **prefixes each manual's env vars with the manual name**. The `figma` manual therefore needs the key as **`figma_FIGMA_API_KEY`**, not bare `FIGMA_API_KEY`.\n\n**Fix**:\n\n```bash\n# In .env (illustrative — do not paste the token into chat output):\nfigma_FIGMA_API_KEY=figd_your_token_here\n```\n\nSet `figma_FIGMA_API_KEY` in `.env`, then restart Code Mode so the manual reloads. Never expose the token in user-facing output.\n\n---\n\n### Issue: Framelink `figma` tools missing in Code Mode\n\n**Symptoms**: `call_tool_chain()` cannot find any `figma.figma_<tool>` to call.\n\n**Diagnosis / Fix** (discover first, never guess names):\n\n1. Confirm the `figma` manual is registered in `.utcp_config.json` (`manual_call_templates`), stdio, `npx -y figma-developer-mcp@latest --stdio`.\n2. Ensure `figma_FIGMA_API_KEY` is set in `.env` (see the row above).\n3. **Restart Code Mode** so the manual loads.\n4. Discover the real surface before invoking:\n   ```text\n   list_tools()        # filter by the \"figma\" prefix\n   search_tools(...)   # find a tool by intent\n   tool_info(...)      # confirm the exact name + params\n   ```\n5. Call with the prefixed naming `figma.figma_<tool>`. Do not claim a tool works until discovery confirms it.\n\n---\n\n## 10. ERROR / SYMPTOM REFERENCE\n\n| Symptom | Likely cause | Fix |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| `figma-ds-cli: command not found` | Not installed, or npm global bin not on PATH | `npm i -g figma-ds-cli`; fix PATH; never `npm i -g figma-cli` |\n| `figma` works but figma-ds-cli verbs fail | Installed the unrelated unic/`figma-cli` (bin `figma`) | Uninstall `figma-cli`; install `figma-ds-cli`; verify silships |\n| Only `figma-ds-cli` present, no `figma-cli` | npm build ships only `figma-ds-cli`; dual-bin is repo-only | Normal — use `figma-ds-cli` as canonical |\n| Errors on old Node | Node <18 | `nvm install 18 && nvm use 18` |\n| Figma Desktop not found | Desktop not installed (no cloud fallback) | Install Figma Desktop |\n| Connect/doc commands fail | Figma Desktop not running or no file open | Open Figma Desktop with a file, keep it focused |\n| `connect --safe` won't bridge | FigCli plugin not imported / not open | Import `plugin/manifest.json` once; keep FigCli open |\n| Yolo patch fails | Permissions / Full Disk Access / admin | Grant access or use `--safe`; `unpatch` to revert |\n| Yolo broke after Figma update | Update replaced patched `app.asar` | `figma-ds-cli unpatch`, then re-connect (prefer `--safe`) |\n| Daemon `Unauthorized` | `X-Daemon-Token` mismatch | `daemon diagnose` then `daemon restart` (never delete token) |\n| Daemon unreachable on 3456 | Idle timeout / crash / port owned | `daemon restart`/`reconnect`; identify 3456 owner before reuse |\n| CDP port 9222 conflict | Yolo uses fixed 9222; another tool holds it | Identify owner with `lsof`; free it or use `--safe` |\n| Code Mode \"variable not found\" | Missing `figma_` env prefix | Set `figma_FIGMA_API_KEY` in `.env`; restart Code Mode |\n| `figma` tools missing in Code Mode | Manual not loaded / not discovered | Confirm config + `.env`, restart, `list_tools()`/`tool_info()` |\n\n---\n\n## 11. COMMON SOLUTIONS CHECKLIST\n\nBefore escalating, confirm:\n\n- [ ] `figma-ds-cli` is the binary in use (NOT the unrelated unic `figma-cli`).\n- [ ] Node is **>=18** (`node --version`).\n- [ ] Figma Desktop is **installed, open, and has a file open**.\n- [ ] A connect mode completed — safe plugin (default) imported and FigCli kept open, or yolo consented + patched.\n- [ ] `daemon status` is healthy (`diagnose` -> `restart` -> `reconnect` if not).\n- [ ] The daemon endpoint (`127.0.0.1:3456`) and token file exist; the token was never printed.\n- [ ] For Code Mode: `figma_FIGMA_API_KEY` is set in `.env`, Code Mode was restarted, and tools were discovered before calling.\n- [ ] No port conflict on 3456 or (yolo) 9222 — owner identified before any kill.\n- [ ] Examples were verified against the live `--help` surface, not assumed.\n\n---\n\n## 12. ESCALATION\n\nStop and escalate to the user (with the effect and a one-line rollback) when a quick fix is not safe to choose unilaterally:\n\n- The binary is **missing or ambiguous** — ask whether to install `figma-ds-cli` (npm) or the silships repo build; do not guess.\n- A **yolo patch**, an **unpatch**, or any **destructive verb** is needed to recover — describe the effect and rollback, then wait for confirmation.\n- A **port conflict** can only be cleared by stopping an unidentified process — confirm the owner first.\n- The **optional Figma MCP** is requested but no token / `figma` manual is configured — surface the `.env` requirement; never paste credentials.\n- A failure persists on **Linux/Windows** — those platforms are experimental and unverified; flag the limitation rather than improvising an unsupported fix.\n\nWhen reporting a bug upstream, include: the binary in use and version (`figma-ds-cli --version`), Node version, platform (macOS supported), connect mode (safe/yolo), `daemon diagnose` output (token redacted), and the full error with `2>&1`.\n\n---\n\n## 13. REFERENCES\n\n- [figma_cli_reference.md](figma_cli_reference.md) - binary identity, Node/macOS baseline, Figma Desktop requirement, connect modes, and the daemon model.\n- [tool_surface.md](tool_surface.md) - the read-only / mutating / destructive command taxonomy and the gating rules.\n- [mcp_wiring.md](mcp_wiring.md) - the optional Figma MCP (Framelink `figma`) via Code Mode: the registered manual, the `.env` token, and discovery.\n- [INSTALL_GUIDE.md](../INSTALL_GUIDE.md) - install steps and binary verification.\n- [SKILL.md](../SKILL.md) - the skill contract this reference supports.\n- Code Mode transport for the optional MCP: [mcp-code-mode SKILL.md](../../mcp-code-mode/SKILL.md). Browser-debugging owner for port 9222 conflicts: [mcp-chrome-devtools SKILL.md](../../mcp-chrome-devtools/SKILL.md).\n- Upstream: [silships/figma-cli](https://github.com/silships/figma-cli) (npm `figma-ds-cli`, MIT). [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/) (>=18). This skill does not vendor either.\n\n> **Note**: Most failures are upstream of any Figma operation — wrong package under the colliding `figma-cli` name, Node <18, Figma Desktop not open, an incomplete connect mode, or a missing Code Mode env prefix. Verify the binary, Desktop state, and daemon health before deeper diagnosis, and confirm every illustrative command against the live `--help` surface.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":479,"totalLines":479,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/references/troubleshooting.md","time":{"start":1781459254423,"end":1781459254427}},"id":"prt_ec73efc96001h5nAUHk6S7E7fB","sessionID":"ses_138c2bb01ffeUjkBZZt6lKZbis","messageID":"msg_ec73eecf1001M64MZwQAoNqVRp"}}
