{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781459415291,"sessionID":"ses_138c2bb01ffeUjkBZZt6lKZbis","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_b8963e9d8f5e4ed7b1364489","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/mcp-figma/feature_catalog/feature_catalog.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/mcp-figma/feature_catalog/feature_catalog.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"mcp-figma: Feature Catalog\"\n3: description: \"Unified capability inventory for the mcp-figma skill, covering figma-ds-cli connect/daemon, inspect, design-system extract/import, render/create, tokens/variables, export, a11y/analysis, and the optional Figma MCP via Code Mode — each capability tagged read-only, mutating, or destructive.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"figma cli\"\n6:   - \"figma-ds-cli\"\n7:   - \"feature catalog\"\n8: last_updated: \"2026-06-14\"\n9: ---\n10: \n11: # mcp-figma: Feature Catalog\n12: \n13: This document is the canonical capability inventory for the `mcp-figma` skill. The root catalog acts as the system-level directory: it summarizes each capability area, names the canonical `figma-ds-cli` command for each feature, and tags every command read-only, mutating, or destructive so the gating model is visible at a glance. The skill drives the installed Figma Desktop app from the terminal through the silships `figma-ds-cli` so a coding agent can connect, inspect, author, modify, and export designs, tokens, and components — and **optionally** pull design context out of Figma through a community Figma MCP via Code Mode. The CLI is the primary surface; the MCP is opt-in.\n14: \n15: > **Naming trap (read first).** The canonical binary is **`figma-ds-cli`** (silships, npm, MIT). The npm package literally named **`figma-cli` is an UNRELATED tool** (unic/figma-cli, bin `figma`) — **NEVER `npm i -g figma-cli`**. The `figma-cli` command exists only when installed from the silships repo. This catalog uses `figma-ds-cli` as the canonical command throughout.\n16: \n17: > **Verification note.** Commands below are illustrative and sourced from the figma-cli capability research digest; verify any exact verb, flag, or output with `figma-ds-cli <command> --help` before relying on it. The research flags known doc drift (REFERENCE shows `create rect/circle`, source proves `create frame/icon/image` plus top-level aliases; `voice`/`chat`/`prop combine` appear in docs but were not found in source). Do NOT run `figma-ds-cli` against a live document without verifying the command and its gating class first.\n18: \n19: ---\n20: \n21: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n22: \n23: Use this catalog as the inventory for the live `mcp-figma` surface. The numbered sections below group the skill by capability area so readers can move from a top-level summary into the per-command detail without losing the gating context.\n24: \n25: The capability surface has one hard prerequisite and three working directions, plus an optional context pull. Everything depends on a **connection**: figma-cli drives **Figma Desktop (open with a file)**, with no Figma API key, over a local daemon. From there the **read** direction inspects and exports without changing the document, the **write** direction authors, renders, sets tokens, and imports design systems behind gates, and a small **destructive** subset deletes content behind hard confirms. Underneath the optional last direction sits the community Figma MCP, reached through this repo's Code Mode rather than by anything figma-cli ships.\n26: \n27: A note on what stays out of scope. This skill is the terminal transport, not the design judgment: the look-and-feel decisions belong to `sk-interface-design`. figma-cli does **not** ship or spawn its own MCP (source-verified zero hits) — its daemon is a private HTTP/WebSocket bridge, not an MCP server. The OFFICIAL Figma Dev Mode MCP is out of scope for this release; only the community Framelink `figma` manual is documented as a supported optional path.\n28: \n29: ### Command class tags\n30: \n31: Every command below carries one tag. Local exports are read-only but still write files, so they require an explicit output path and never silently overwrite.\n32: \n33: | Class | Meaning | Default handling |\n34: |---|---|---|\n35: | READ-ONLY | Reads the doc or writes only export files; no document change | Safe default; exports need an explicit output path, no overwrite |\n36: | MUTATING | Changes the Figma document or local app/config state | Gate: confirmation + explicit target |\n37: | DESTRUCTIVE | Deletes document content or resources | Confirm + explicit target + one-line rollback |\n38: | ARBITRARY | `eval` / `raw` / `run` can do anything | Treat as mutating; review the code/command first |\n39: \n40: ### Capability areas\n41: \n42: | Capability area | Direction | Default safety |\n43: |---|---|---|\n44: | Connect and daemon | Foundation | Safe `connect --safe` default; yolo patch gated; daemon checks read-only |\n45: | Inspect | READ | Always safe, nothing is written to the document |\n46: | Design-system extract and import | READ (extract) feeding judgment / MUTATING (import) | Extract read-only with explicit output; import gated |\n47: | Render and create | WRITE | Gated: confirmation + explicit target |\n48: | Tokens and variables | WRITE (+ destructive deletes) | Gated; `var delete-all` / `delete-batch` are destructive |\n49: | Export | READ | Safe; explicit output path, no silent overwrite |\n50: | A11y and analysis | READ | Always safe |\n51: | Optional MCP context | READ (opt-in) | Code Mode; verify the manual and tools live first |\n52: \n53: ---\n54: \n55: ## 2. CONNECT AND DAEMON\n56: \n57: Bring up and maintain the link between the terminal and Figma Desktop. Safe plugin mode is the default; the yolo patch that edits Figma's `app.asar` is gated behind explicit consent and a stated rollback. The daemon is a local HTTP server on `127.0.0.1:3456` (not a Unix socket), authed with `X-Daemon-Token` from `~/.figma-ds-cli/.daemon-token`, idle ~60 min, not reboot-persistent. Daemon status/diagnose verbs are read-only; start/stop/restart and connect/unpatch change app or daemon state.\n58: \n59: | Feature | One-line description | Class | figma-ds-cli command |\n60: |---|---|---|---|\n61: | Safe connect (default) | FigCli plugin bridge, no patch; import `plugin/manifest.json` once, keep the plugin open | MUTATING (app-level) | `figma-ds-cli connect --safe` |\n62: | Yolo connect (gated) | Patches Figma `app.asar` + codesigns + CDP port 9222; needs consent + rollback | MUTATING (app-level) | `figma-ds-cli connect` |\n63: | Unpatch (rollback) | Restores the original `app.asar` string after a yolo patch | MUTATING (app-level) | `figma-ds-cli unpatch` |\n64: | Connection status | Reports whether the CLI is connected to Desktop | READ-ONLY | `figma-ds-cli status` |\n65: | Diagnose | Diagnoses the connection/setup without changing it | READ-ONLY | `figma-ds-cli diagnose` |\n66: | Daemon status | Reports daemon health (HTTP `127.0.0.1:3456`, token present) | READ-ONLY | `figma-ds-cli daemon status [--debug]` |\n67: | Daemon diagnose | Diagnoses daemon/token issues (e.g. \"Unauthorized\") | READ-ONLY | `figma-ds-cli daemon diagnose` |\n68: | Daemon start / stop / restart | Brings the local daemon up, down, or recycles it | MUTATING (app-level) | `figma-ds-cli daemon start [--force] \\| stop \\| restart` |\n69: | Daemon reconnect | Re-establishes the Desktop link without a full restart | MUTATING (app-level) | `figma-ds-cli daemon reconnect` |\n70: | init-agent (off by default) | Writes `AGENTS.md` + `.cursor/rules/figma-cli.mdc` into the repo; never run by default | MUTATING (app-level) | `figma-ds-cli init-agent [--tool claude\\|cursor\\|both] [--force]` |\n71: \n72: See [`01--connect-and-daemon/connect-and-daemon.md`](01--connect-and-daemon/connect-and-daemon.md) for the safe-vs-yolo gate, the daemon model, and the token-handling rules.\n73: \n74: ---\n75: \n76: ## 3. INSPECT\n77: \n78: Read the live document without changing it: list and find nodes, get properties, walk a node tree and its bindings, list collections and slots. These are the safe default and the input to design work and to any later gated verb.\n79: \n80: | Feature | One-line description | Class | figma-ds-cli command |\n81: |---|---|---|---|\n82: | Find nodes | Locates nodes matching a query | READ-ONLY | `figma-ds-cli find <query>` |\n83: | Get node | Returns a node's properties | READ-ONLY | `figma-ds-cli get <node>` |\n84: | Inspect node | Inspects a node's full property set | READ-ONLY | `figma-ds-cli inspect <node>` |\n85: | Node tree | Prints the node hierarchy | READ-ONLY | `figma-ds-cli node tree [<node>]` |\n86: | Node bindings | Lists variable bindings on a node | READ-ONLY | `figma-ds-cli node bindings <node>` |\n87: | Canvas info / next | Reports canvas state / next placement slot | READ-ONLY | `figma-ds-cli canvas info \\| next` |\n88: | Spec | Emits a node/document spec | READ-ONLY | `figma-ds-cli spec [<node>]` |\n89: | Files | Lists known files in the session | READ-ONLY | `figma-ds-cli files` |\n90: | Slot list | Lists component slots | READ-ONLY | `figma-ds-cli slot list <component>` |\n91: | Bind list | Lists existing variable bindings | READ-ONLY | `figma-ds-cli bind list` |\n92: \n93: See [`02--inspect/inspect.md`](02--inspect/inspect.md) for the read-only inspect surface and its session prerequisite.\n94: \n95: ---\n96: \n97: ## 4. DESIGN-SYSTEM EXTRACT AND IMPORT\n98: \n99: Move a design system out of Figma (read-only) or into Figma (gated). `extract` produces a `DESIGN.md` with 11 sections including a machine-readable `design-tokens` JSON block, and auto-splits very large structure into a `DESIGN-structure/` folder (handle multi-file output). `import` ingests Tailwind config, CSS variables, W3C/Style-Dictionary `tokens.json`, or a Storybook source. Extract is read-only but writes a file, so it needs an explicit output path and must not silently overwrite; import changes the document and is gated.\n100: \n101: | Feature | One-line description | Class | figma-ds-cli command |\n102: |---|---|---|---|\n103: | Extract DESIGN.md | Reads the design system to a `DESIGN.md` (11 sections + token JSON; auto-splits) | READ-ONLY (explicit output) | `figma-ds-cli extract [output] [--pages --sections --selection --split/--no-split]` |\n104: | Import design system | Imports Tailwind/CSS/tokens.json/Storybook into Figma collections | MUTATING | `figma-ds-cli import <source> [-c <collection> --save --type <tailwind\\|css\\|tokens\\|storybook\\|designmd> --print-context]` |\n105: \n106: See [`03--design-system-extract-and-import/design-system-extract-and-import.md`](03--design-system-extract-and-import/design-system-extract-and-import.md) for the extract output rule and the import gate.\n107: \n108: ---\n109: \n110: ## 5. RENDER AND CREATE\n111: \n112: Author content in the document: render JSX-described nodes, create frames/icons/images and primitives, lay out and arrange, duplicate, convert to components, and generate variants and combos. Every verb here changes the document and is gated. `--dry-run` variants of arrange/unstack/use/combos are read-only previews. Prefer `render`/`render-batch` over `eval` for visual nodes (eval bypasses positioning).\n113: \n114: | Feature | One-line description | Class | figma-ds-cli command |\n115: |---|---|---|---|\n116: | Render JSX | Renders a JSX-described node into the document | MUTATING | `figma-ds-cli render <jsx>` |\n117: | Render batch | Renders multiple nodes in one pass | MUTATING | `figma-ds-cli render-batch <source>` |\n118: | Create frame / icon / image | Creates a frame, icon, or image node (source-verified primitives) | MUTATING | `figma-ds-cli create frame\\|icon\\|image ...` |\n119: | Create primitives (aliases) | Top-level shape/text/group aliases | MUTATING | `figma-ds-cli rect\\|ellipse\\|text\\|line\\|component\\|group\\|autolayout ...` |\n120: | Set property | Sets a property (fill, etc.; supports `var:name`) | MUTATING | `figma-ds-cli set <prop> <value>` |\n121: | Layout verbs | Sizing, padding, gap, align on a node | MUTATING | `figma-ds-cli sizing\\|padding\\|gap\\|align <node> ...` |\n122: | Arrange / unstack | Arranges or unstacks nodes (preview with `--dry-run`) | MUTATING | `figma-ds-cli arrange\\|unstack <node> [--dry-run]` |\n123: | Duplicate | Duplicates a node | MUTATING | `figma-ds-cli duplicate <node>` |\n124: | To component | Converts a node into a component | MUTATING | `figma-ds-cli node to-component <node>` |\n125: | Variants / sizes / combos | Generates component variants, sizes, or combos | MUTATING | `figma-ds-cli variants\\|sizes\\|combos ... [--dry-run]` |\n126: | shadcn add | Adds shadcn primitives into the document | MUTATING | `figma-ds-cli shadcn add <component>` |\n127: | Screenshot/recreate from URL | Captures or recreates a design from a URL | MUTATING | `figma-ds-cli screenshot-url \\| recreate-url <url>` |\n128: | Arbitrary execution | Runs arbitrary code/commands — can do anything; review first | ARBITRARY | `figma-ds-cli eval\\|raw\\|run ...` |\n129: \n130: See [`04--render-and-create/render-and-create.md`](04--render-and-create/render-and-create.md) for the authoring surface, the dry-run previews, and the arbitrary-execution caveat.\n131: \n132: ---\n133: \n134: ## 6. TOKENS AND VARIABLES\n135: \n136: Manage Figma variables and collections, bind `var:name` references, and visualize tokens. Reads and binds are read-only or gated; create/bind/set/rename/visualize change the document; bulk deletes are destructive and require an explicit target and rollback. Token binding uses `var:name` (e.g. `bg=\"var:card\"`), `var:collection:name` to pin a collection, or `render --collection <name>`.\n137: \n138: | Feature | One-line description | Class | figma-ds-cli command |\n139: |---|---|---|---|\n140: | List variables / collections | Lists variables, collections, or finds a variable | READ-ONLY | `figma-ds-cli var list \\| var find <q> \\| collections list` |\n141: | Token overlap | Reports overlapping/conflicting tokens | READ-ONLY | `figma-ds-cli tokens overlap` |\n142: | Create variable | Creates a variable | MUTATING | `figma-ds-cli var create <name> <value>` |\n143: | Bind variable | Binds a variable to a node property | MUTATING | `figma-ds-cli var bind <node> <prop> <var> \\| bind <node> <var>` |\n144: | Set / rename variable | Sets a variable value or renames it | MUTATING | `figma-ds-cli var set\\|rename <name> ...` |\n145: | Visualize tokens | Renders a token visualization | MUTATING | `figma-ds-cli var visualize` |\n146: | Use / theme | Applies a collection or theme | MUTATING | `figma-ds-cli use\\|theme <name> [--dry-run]` |\n147: | Delete one variable | Deletes a single variable | DESTRUCTIVE | `figma-ds-cli delete\\|remove <node-or-var>` |\n148: | Delete all variables | Deletes every variable — requires confirm + rollback | DESTRUCTIVE | `figma-ds-cli var delete-all` |\n149: | Delete variable batch | Deletes a batch of variables by id | DESTRUCTIVE | `figma-ds-cli var delete-batch <ids>` |\n150: \n151: See [`05--tokens-and-variables/tokens-and-variables.md`](05--tokens-and-variables/tokens-and-variables.md) for the bind syntax and the destructive delete gate.\n152: \n153: ---\n154: \n155: ## 7. EXPORT\n156: \n157: Write assets and code out of the document: PNG/SVG, CSS, Tailwind, JSX, and Storybook. Export is read-only with respect to the Figma document but writes local files, so it always requires an explicit output path and must never silently overwrite an existing file.\n158: \n159: | Feature | One-line description | Class | figma-ds-cli command |\n160: |---|---|---|---|\n161: | Export asset | Exports a node as a screenshot/PNG/SVG to an explicit path | READ-ONLY (explicit output) | `figma-ds-cli export screenshot\\|node <node> <output>` |\n162: | Export CSS / Tailwind | Exports node styles as CSS or Tailwind | READ-ONLY (explicit output) | `figma-ds-cli export css\\|tailwind <node> <output>` |\n163: | Export JSX | Exports a node as JSX | READ-ONLY (explicit output) | `figma-ds-cli export-jsx <node> <output>` |\n164: | Export Storybook | Exports components as Storybook stories | READ-ONLY (explicit output) | `figma-ds-cli export-storybook <output>` |\n165: \n166: See [`07--export/export.md`](07--export/export.md) for the export surface and the explicit-output, no-overwrite rule.\n167: \n168: ---\n169: \n170: ## 8. A11Y AND ANALYSIS\n171: \n172: Audit and analyze the document without changing it: accessibility checks, general analysis, gradient extraction (read-only when not applied), and URL analysis. All read-only. `gradient extract --apply-to` writes the gradient back and is therefore mutating, so it belongs to the render/create surface, not here.\n173: \n174: | Feature | One-line description | Class | figma-ds-cli command |\n175: |---|---|---|---|\n176: | A11y audit | Runs accessibility checks on nodes/document | READ-ONLY | `figma-ds-cli a11y ...` |\n177: | Analyze | Runs general analysis on the document | READ-ONLY | `figma-ds-cli analyze ...` |\n178: | Analyze URL | Analyzes a design at a URL | READ-ONLY | `figma-ds-cli analyze-url <url>` |\n179: | Verify | Verifies the result of a prior operation | READ-ONLY | `figma-ds-cli verify ...` |\n180: | Gradient extract (read) | Extracts a gradient without applying it | READ-ONLY | `figma-ds-cli gradient extract <node>` |\n181: \n182: See [`06--a11y-and-analysis/a11y-and-analysis.md`](06--a11y-and-analysis/a11y-and-analysis.md) for the read-only audit surface and the applied-gradient boundary.\n183: \n184: ---\n185: \n186: ## 9. OPTIONAL MCP CONTEXT\n187: \n188: The skill works fully with the CLI alone. When the agent must pull design context FROM Figma as model input, use the **community Framelink `figma-developer-mcp` manual already registered as `figma` in this repo's Code Mode** (`.utcp_config.json`, stdio). It needs a Figma personal token in `.env` as `figma_FIGMA_API_KEY` (Code Mode prefixes the manual name). Calls go through `call_tool_chain()` with the naming `figma.figma_<tool>`; always discover first with `search_tools()` / `tool_info()` before invoking, and never claim a tool works until discovery confirms it. The OFFICIAL Figma Dev Mode MCP is out of scope for this release and is not a supported path (a future option only).\n189: \n190: | Feature | One-line description | Class | Invocation |\n191: |---|---|---|---|\n192: | Discover MCP tools | Confirms the `figma` manual and its tool names before use | READ-ONLY | `search_tools()` / `tool_info()` (Code Mode) |\n193: | Pull design context | Calls a Framelink `figma` tool to pull design data into the agent | READ-ONLY (opt-in) | `call_tool_chain()` with `figma.figma_<tool>` |\n194: \n195: See [`08--optional-mcp/optional-mcp-context.md`](08--optional-mcp/optional-mcp-context.md) for the Code Mode discovery-first contract and the Dev Mode out-of-scope boundary.\n196: \n197: ---\n198: \n199: ## 10. CAPABILITY COUNT SUMMARY\n200: \n201: Each capability area maps to exactly one per-feature file in its numbered category folder. The command count is the decision-relevant command surface digested per area, not the per-feature file count.\n202: \n203: | Section | Area | Commands listed | Per-feature file |\n204: |---|---|---|---|\n205: | 2 | Connect and daemon | 10 | `01--connect-and-daemon/connect-and-daemon.md` |\n206: | 3 | Inspect | 10 | `02--inspect/inspect.md` |\n207: | 4 | Design-system extract and import | 2 | `03--design-system-extract-and-import/design-system-extract-and-import.md` |\n208: | 5 | Render and create | 12 | `04--render-and-create/render-and-create.md` |\n209: | 6 | Tokens and variables | 10 | `05--tokens-and-variables/tokens-and-variables.md` |\n210: | 7 | Export | 4 | `07--export/export.md` |\n211: | 8 | A11y and analysis | 5 | `06--a11y-and-analysis/a11y-and-analysis.md` |\n212: | 9 | Optional MCP context | 2 | `08--optional-mcp/optional-mcp-context.md` |\n213: | **Total** | **8 capability areas** | **55 command rows** | **8 per-feature files** |\n214: \n215: > Counts cover the decision-relevant commands digested in the figma-cli capability research; the full per-command flag surface (≈130 rows) lives in the research raw output and is not reproduced here. The per-feature file count MUST equal the 8 capability areas; keep them in sync as areas are added or revised. Verify any command, flag, or class against `figma-ds-cli --help` before relying on it.\n\n(End of file - total 215 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"mcp-figma: Feature Catalog\"\ndescription: \"Unified capability inventory for the mcp-figma skill, covering figma-ds-cli connect/daemon, inspect, design-system extract/import, render/create, tokens/variables, export, a11y/analysis, and the optional Figma MCP via Code Mode — each capability tagged read-only, mutating, or destructive.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"figma cli\"\n  - \"figma-ds-cli\"\n  - \"feature catalog\"\nlast_updated: \"2026-06-14\"\n---\n\n# mcp-figma: Feature Catalog\n\nThis document is the canonical capability inventory for the `mcp-figma` skill. The root catalog acts as the system-level directory: it summarizes each capability area, names the canonical `figma-ds-cli` command for each feature, and tags every command read-only, mutating, or destructive so the gating model is visible at a glance. The skill drives the installed Figma Desktop app from the terminal through the silships `figma-ds-cli` so a coding agent can connect, inspect, author, modify, and export designs, tokens, and components — and **optionally** pull design context out of Figma through a community Figma MCP via Code Mode. The CLI is the primary surface; the MCP is opt-in.\n\n> **Naming trap (read first).** The canonical binary is **`figma-ds-cli`** (silships, npm, MIT). The npm package literally named **`figma-cli` is an UNRELATED tool** (unic/figma-cli, bin `figma`) — **NEVER `npm i -g figma-cli`**. The `figma-cli` command exists only when installed from the silships repo. This catalog uses `figma-ds-cli` as the canonical command throughout.\n\n> **Verification note.** Commands below are illustrative and sourced from the figma-cli capability research digest; verify any exact verb, flag, or output with `figma-ds-cli <command> --help` before relying on it. The research flags known doc drift (REFERENCE shows `create rect/circle`, source proves `create frame/icon/image` plus top-level aliases; `voice`/`chat`/`prop combine` appear in docs but were not found in source). Do NOT run `figma-ds-cli` against a live document without verifying the command and its gating class first.\n\n---\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/mcp-figma/feature_catalog/feature_catalog.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"mcp-figma: Feature Catalog\"\ndescription: \"Unified capability inventory for the mcp-figma skill, covering figma-ds-cli connect/daemon, inspect, design-system extract/import, render/create, tokens/variables, export, a11y/analysis, and the optional Figma MCP via Code Mode — each capability tagged read-only, mutating, or destructive.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"figma cli\"\n  - \"figma-ds-cli\"\n  - \"feature catalog\"\nlast_updated: \"2026-06-14\"\n---\n\n# mcp-figma: Feature Catalog\n\nThis document is the canonical capability inventory for the `mcp-figma` skill. The root catalog acts as the system-level directory: it summarizes each capability area, names the canonical `figma-ds-cli` command for each feature, and tags every command read-only, mutating, or destructive so the gating model is visible at a glance. The skill drives the installed Figma Desktop app from the terminal through the silships `figma-ds-cli` so a coding agent can connect, inspect, author, modify, and export designs, tokens, and components — and **optionally** pull design context out of Figma through a community Figma MCP via Code Mode. The CLI is the primary surface; the MCP is opt-in.\n\n> **Naming trap (read first).** The canonical binary is **`figma-ds-cli`** (silships, npm, MIT). The npm package literally named **`figma-cli` is an UNRELATED tool** (unic/figma-cli, bin `figma`) — **NEVER `npm i -g figma-cli`**. The `figma-cli` command exists only when installed from the silships repo. This catalog uses `figma-ds-cli` as the canonical command throughout.\n\n> **Verification note.** Commands below are illustrative and sourced from the figma-cli capability research digest; verify any exact verb, flag, or output with `figma-ds-cli <command> --help` before relying on it. The research flags known doc drift (REFERENCE shows `create rect/circle`, source proves `create frame/icon/image` plus top-level aliases; `voice`/`chat`/`prop combine` appear in docs but were not found in source). Do NOT run `figma-ds-cli` against a live document without verifying the command and its gating class first.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nUse this catalog as the inventory for the live `mcp-figma` surface. The numbered sections below group the skill by capability area so readers can move from a top-level summary into the per-command detail without losing the gating context.\n\nThe capability surface has one hard prerequisite and three working directions, plus an optional context pull. Everything depends on a **connection**: figma-cli drives **Figma Desktop (open with a file)**, with no Figma API key, over a local daemon. From there the **read** direction inspects and exports without changing the document, the **write** direction authors, renders, sets tokens, and imports design systems behind gates, and a small **destructive** subset deletes content behind hard confirms. Underneath the optional last direction sits the community Figma MCP, reached through this repo's Code Mode rather than by anything figma-cli ships.\n\nA note on what stays out of scope. This skill is the terminal transport, not the design judgment: the look-and-feel decisions belong to `sk-interface-design`. figma-cli does **not** ship or spawn its own MCP (source-verified zero hits) — its daemon is a private HTTP/WebSocket bridge, not an MCP server. The OFFICIAL Figma Dev Mode MCP is out of scope for this release; only the community Framelink `figma` manual is documented as a supported optional path.\n\n### Command class tags\n\nEvery command below carries one tag. Local exports are read-only but still write files, so they require an explicit output path and never silently overwrite.\n\n| Class | Meaning | Default handling |\n|---|---|---|\n| READ-ONLY | Reads the doc or writes only export files; no document change | Safe default; exports need an explicit output path, no overwrite |\n| MUTATING | Changes the Figma document or local app/config state | Gate: confirmation + explicit target |\n| DESTRUCTIVE | Deletes document content or resources | Confirm + explicit target + one-line rollback |\n| ARBITRARY | `eval` / `raw` / `run` can do anything | Treat as mutating; review the code/command first |\n\n### Capability areas\n\n| Capability area | Direction | Default safety |\n|---|---|---|\n| Connect and daemon | Foundation | Safe `connect --safe` default; yolo patch gated; daemon checks read-only |\n| Inspect | READ | Always safe, nothing is written to the document |\n| Design-system extract and import | READ (extract) feeding judgment / MUTATING (import) | Extract read-only with explicit output; import gated |\n| Render and create | WRITE | Gated: confirmation + explicit target |\n| Tokens and variables | WRITE (+ destructive deletes) | Gated; `var delete-all` / `delete-batch` are destructive |\n| Export | READ | Safe; explicit output path, no silent overwrite |\n| A11y and analysis | READ | Always safe |\n| Optional MCP context | READ (opt-in) | Code Mode; verify the manual and tools live first |\n\n---\n\n## 2. CONNECT AND DAEMON\n\nBring up and maintain the link between the terminal and Figma Desktop. Safe plugin mode is the default; the yolo patch that edits Figma's `app.asar` is gated behind explicit consent and a stated rollback. The daemon is a local HTTP server on `127.0.0.1:3456` (not a Unix socket), authed with `X-Daemon-Token` from `~/.figma-ds-cli/.daemon-token`, idle ~60 min, not reboot-persistent. Daemon status/diagnose verbs are read-only; start/stop/restart and connect/unpatch change app or daemon state.\n\n| Feature | One-line description | Class | figma-ds-cli command |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Safe connect (default) | FigCli plugin bridge, no patch; import `plugin/manifest.json` once, keep the plugin open | MUTATING (app-level) | `figma-ds-cli connect --safe` |\n| Yolo connect (gated) | Patches Figma `app.asar` + codesigns + CDP port 9222; needs consent + rollback | MUTATING (app-level) | `figma-ds-cli connect` |\n| Unpatch (rollback) | Restores the original `app.asar` string after a yolo patch | MUTATING (app-level) | `figma-ds-cli unpatch` |\n| Connection status | Reports whether the CLI is connected to Desktop | READ-ONLY | `figma-ds-cli status` |\n| Diagnose | Diagnoses the connection/setup without changing it | READ-ONLY | `figma-ds-cli diagnose` |\n| Daemon status | Reports daemon health (HTTP `127.0.0.1:3456`, token present) | READ-ONLY | `figma-ds-cli daemon status [--debug]` |\n| Daemon diagnose | Diagnoses daemon/token issues (e.g. \"Unauthorized\") | READ-ONLY | `figma-ds-cli daemon diagnose` |\n| Daemon start / stop / restart | Brings the local daemon up, down, or recycles it | MUTATING (app-level) | `figma-ds-cli daemon start [--force] \\| stop \\| restart` |\n| Daemon reconnect | Re-establishes the Desktop link without a full restart | MUTATING (app-level) | `figma-ds-cli daemon reconnect` |\n| init-agent (off by default) | Writes `AGENTS.md` + `.cursor/rules/figma-cli.mdc` into the repo; never run by default | MUTATING (app-level) | `figma-ds-cli init-agent [--tool claude\\|cursor\\|both] [--force]` |\n\nSee [`01--connect-and-daemon/connect-and-daemon.md`](01--connect-and-daemon/connect-and-daemon.md) for the safe-vs-yolo gate, the daemon model, and the token-handling rules.\n\n---\n\n## 3. INSPECT\n\nRead the live document without changing it: list and find nodes, get properties, walk a node tree and its bindings, list collections and slots. These are the safe default and the input to design work and to any later gated verb.\n\n| Feature | One-line description | Class | figma-ds-cli command |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Find nodes | Locates nodes matching a query | READ-ONLY | `figma-ds-cli find <query>` |\n| Get node | Returns a node's properties | READ-ONLY | `figma-ds-cli get <node>` |\n| Inspect node | Inspects a node's full property set | READ-ONLY | `figma-ds-cli inspect <node>` |\n| Node tree | Prints the node hierarchy | READ-ONLY | `figma-ds-cli node tree [<node>]` |\n| Node bindings | Lists variable bindings on a node | READ-ONLY | `figma-ds-cli node bindings <node>` |\n| Canvas info / next | Reports canvas state / next placement slot | READ-ONLY | `figma-ds-cli canvas info \\| next` |\n| Spec | Emits a node/document spec | READ-ONLY | `figma-ds-cli spec [<node>]` |\n| Files | Lists known files in the session | READ-ONLY | `figma-ds-cli files` |\n| Slot list | Lists component slots | READ-ONLY | `figma-ds-cli slot list <component>` |\n| Bind list | Lists existing variable bindings | READ-ONLY | `figma-ds-cli bind list` |\n\nSee [`02--inspect/inspect.md`](02--inspect/inspect.md) for the read-only inspect surface and its session prerequisite.\n\n---\n\n## 4. DESIGN-SYSTEM EXTRACT AND IMPORT\n\nMove a design system out of Figma (read-only) or into Figma (gated). `extract` produces a `DESIGN.md` with 11 sections including a machine-readable `design-tokens` JSON block, and auto-splits very large structure into a `DESIGN-structure/` folder (handle multi-file output). `import` ingests Tailwind config, CSS variables, W3C/Style-Dictionary `tokens.json`, or a Storybook source. Extract is read-only but writes a file, so it needs an explicit output path and must not silently overwrite; import changes the document and is gated.\n\n| Feature | One-line description | Class | figma-ds-cli command |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Extract DESIGN.md | Reads the design system to a `DESIGN.md` (11 sections + token JSON; auto-splits) | READ-ONLY (explicit output) | `figma-ds-cli extract [output] [--pages --sections --selection --split/--no-split]` |\n| Import design system | Imports Tailwind/CSS/tokens.json/Storybook into Figma collections | MUTATING | `figma-ds-cli import <source> [-c <collection> --save --type <tailwind\\|css\\|tokens\\|storybook\\|designmd> --print-context]` |\n\nSee [`03--design-system-extract-and-import/design-system-extract-and-import.md`](03--design-system-extract-and-import/design-system-extract-and-import.md) for the extract output rule and the import gate.\n\n---\n\n## 5. RENDER AND CREATE\n\nAuthor content in the document: render JSX-described nodes, create frames/icons/images and primitives, lay out and arrange, duplicate, convert to components, and generate variants and combos. Every verb here changes the document and is gated. `--dry-run` variants of arrange/unstack/use/combos are read-only previews. Prefer `render`/`render-batch` over `eval` for visual nodes (eval bypasses positioning).\n\n| Feature | One-line description | Class | figma-ds-cli command |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Render JSX | Renders a JSX-described node into the document | MUTATING | `figma-ds-cli render <jsx>` |\n| Render batch | Renders multiple nodes in one pass | MUTATING | `figma-ds-cli render-batch <source>` |\n| Create frame / icon / image | Creates a frame, icon, or image node (source-verified primitives) | MUTATING | `figma-ds-cli create frame\\|icon\\|image ...` |\n| Create primitives (aliases) | Top-level shape/text/group aliases | MUTATING | `figma-ds-cli rect\\|ellipse\\|text\\|line\\|component\\|group\\|autolayout ...` |\n| Set property | Sets a property (fill, etc.; supports `var:name`) | MUTATING | `figma-ds-cli set <prop> <value>` |\n| Layout verbs | Sizing, padding, gap, align on a node | MUTATING | `figma-ds-cli sizing\\|padding\\|gap\\|align <node> ...` |\n| Arrange / unstack | Arranges or unstacks nodes (preview with `--dry-run`) | MUTATING | `figma-ds-cli arrange\\|unstack <node> [--dry-run]` |\n| Duplicate | Duplicates a node | MUTATING | `figma-ds-cli duplicate <node>` |\n| To component | Converts a node into a component | MUTATING | `figma-ds-cli node to-component <node>` |\n| Variants / sizes / combos | Generates component variants, sizes, or combos | MUTATING | `figma-ds-cli variants\\|sizes\\|combos ... [--dry-run]` |\n| shadcn add | Adds shadcn primitives into the document | MUTATING | `figma-ds-cli shadcn add <component>` |\n| Screenshot/recreate from URL | Captures or recreates a design from a URL | MUTATING | `figma-ds-cli screenshot-url \\| recreate-url <url>` |\n| Arbitrary execution | Runs arbitrary code/commands — can do anything; review first | ARBITRARY | `figma-ds-cli eval\\|raw\\|run ...` |\n\nSee [`04--render-and-create/render-and-create.md`](04--render-and-create/render-and-create.md) for the authoring surface, the dry-run previews, and the arbitrary-execution caveat.\n\n---\n\n## 6. TOKENS AND VARIABLES\n\nManage Figma variables and collections, bind `var:name` references, and visualize tokens. Reads and binds are read-only or gated; create/bind/set/rename/visualize change the document; bulk deletes are destructive and require an explicit target and rollback. Token binding uses `var:name` (e.g. `bg=\"var:card\"`), `var:collection:name` to pin a collection, or `render --collection <name>`.\n\n| Feature | One-line description | Class | figma-ds-cli command |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| List variables / collections | Lists variables, collections, or finds a variable | READ-ONLY | `figma-ds-cli var list \\| var find <q> \\| collections list` |\n| Token overlap | Reports overlapping/conflicting tokens | READ-ONLY | `figma-ds-cli tokens overlap` |\n| Create variable | Creates a variable | MUTATING | `figma-ds-cli var create <name> <value>` |\n| Bind variable | Binds a variable to a node property | MUTATING | `figma-ds-cli var bind <node> <prop> <var> \\| bind <node> <var>` |\n| Set / rename variable | Sets a variable value or renames it | MUTATING | `figma-ds-cli var set\\|rename <name> ...` |\n| Visualize tokens | Renders a token visualization | MUTATING | `figma-ds-cli var visualize` |\n| Use / theme | Applies a collection or theme | MUTATING | `figma-ds-cli use\\|theme <name> [--dry-run]` |\n| Delete one variable | Deletes a single variable | DESTRUCTIVE | `figma-ds-cli delete\\|remove <node-or-var>` |\n| Delete all variables | Deletes every variable — requires confirm + rollback | DESTRUCTIVE | `figma-ds-cli var delete-all` |\n| Delete variable batch | Deletes a batch of variables by id | DESTRUCTIVE | `figma-ds-cli var delete-batch <ids>` |\n\nSee [`05--tokens-and-variables/tokens-and-variables.md`](05--tokens-and-variables/tokens-and-variables.md) for the bind syntax and the destructive delete gate.\n\n---\n\n## 7. EXPORT\n\nWrite assets and code out of the document: PNG/SVG, CSS, Tailwind, JSX, and Storybook. Export is read-only with respect to the Figma document but writes local files, so it always requires an explicit output path and must never silently overwrite an existing file.\n\n| Feature | One-line description | Class | figma-ds-cli command |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Export asset | Exports a node as a screenshot/PNG/SVG to an explicit path | READ-ONLY (explicit output) | `figma-ds-cli export screenshot\\|node <node> <output>` |\n| Export CSS / Tailwind | Exports node styles as CSS or Tailwind | READ-ONLY (explicit output) | `figma-ds-cli export css\\|tailwind <node> <output>` |\n| Export JSX | Exports a node as JSX | READ-ONLY (explicit output) | `figma-ds-cli export-jsx <node> <output>` |\n| Export Storybook | Exports components as Storybook stories | READ-ONLY (explicit output) | `figma-ds-cli export-storybook <output>` |\n\nSee [`07--export/export.md`](07--export/export.md) for the export surface and the explicit-output, no-overwrite rule.\n\n---\n\n## 8. A11Y AND ANALYSIS\n\nAudit and analyze the document without changing it: accessibility checks, general analysis, gradient extraction (read-only when not applied), and URL analysis. All read-only. `gradient extract --apply-to` writes the gradient back and is therefore mutating, so it belongs to the render/create surface, not here.\n\n| Feature | One-line description | Class | figma-ds-cli command |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| A11y audit | Runs accessibility checks on nodes/document | READ-ONLY | `figma-ds-cli a11y ...` |\n| Analyze | Runs general analysis on the document | READ-ONLY | `figma-ds-cli analyze ...` |\n| Analyze URL | Analyzes a design at a URL | READ-ONLY | `figma-ds-cli analyze-url <url>` |\n| Verify | Verifies the result of a prior operation | READ-ONLY | `figma-ds-cli verify ...` |\n| Gradient extract (read) | Extracts a gradient without applying it | READ-ONLY | `figma-ds-cli gradient extract <node>` |\n\nSee [`06--a11y-and-analysis/a11y-and-analysis.md`](06--a11y-and-analysis/a11y-and-analysis.md) for the read-only audit surface and the applied-gradient boundary.\n\n---\n\n## 9. OPTIONAL MCP CONTEXT\n\nThe skill works fully with the CLI alone. When the agent must pull design context FROM Figma as model input, use the **community Framelink `figma-developer-mcp` manual already registered as `figma` in this repo's Code Mode** (`.utcp_config.json`, stdio). It needs a Figma personal token in `.env` as `figma_FIGMA_API_KEY` (Code Mode prefixes the manual name). Calls go through `call_tool_chain()` with the naming `figma.figma_<tool>`; always discover first with `search_tools()` / `tool_info()` before invoking, and never claim a tool works until discovery confirms it. The OFFICIAL Figma Dev Mode MCP is out of scope for this release and is not a supported path (a future option only).\n\n| Feature | One-line description | Class | Invocation |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Discover MCP tools | Confirms the `figma` manual and its tool names before use | READ-ONLY | `search_tools()` / `tool_info()` (Code Mode) |\n| Pull design context | Calls a Framelink `figma` tool to pull design data into the agent | READ-ONLY (opt-in) | `call_tool_chain()` with `figma.figma_<tool>` |\n\nSee [`08--optional-mcp/optional-mcp-context.md`](08--optional-mcp/optional-mcp-context.md) for the Code Mode discovery-first contract and the Dev Mode out-of-scope boundary.\n\n---\n\n## 10. CAPABILITY COUNT SUMMARY\n\nEach capability area maps to exactly one per-feature file in its numbered category folder. The command count is the decision-relevant command surface digested per area, not the per-feature file count.\n\n| Section | Area | Commands listed | Per-feature file |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| 2 | Connect and daemon | 10 | `01--connect-and-daemon/connect-and-daemon.md` |\n| 3 | Inspect | 10 | `02--inspect/inspect.md` |\n| 4 | Design-system extract and import | 2 | `03--design-system-extract-and-import/design-system-extract-and-import.md` |\n| 5 | Render and create | 12 | `04--render-and-create/render-and-create.md` |\n| 6 | Tokens and variables | 10 | `05--tokens-and-variables/tokens-and-variables.md` |\n| 7 | Export | 4 | `07--export/export.md` |\n| 8 | A11y and analysis | 5 | `06--a11y-and-analysis/a11y-and-analysis.md` |\n| 9 | Optional MCP context | 2 | `08--optional-mcp/optional-mcp-context.md` |\n| **Total** | **8 capability areas** | **55 command rows** | **8 per-feature files** |\n\n> Counts cover the decision-relevant commands digested in the figma-cli capability research; the full per-command flag surface (≈130 rows) lives in the research raw output and is not reproduced here. The per-feature file count MUST equal the 8 capability areas; keep them in sync as areas are added or revised. Verify any command, flag, or class against `figma-ds-cli --help` before relying on it.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":215,"totalLines":215,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/feature_catalog/feature_catalog.md","time":{"start":1781459415287,"end":1781459415290}},"id":"prt_ec74170f5001VQChJPiBHn43q9","sessionID":"ses_138c2bb01ffeUjkBZZt6lKZbis","messageID":"msg_ec7416065001x7c4oH0cPXxdQR"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781459415895,"sessionID":"ses_138c2bb01ffeUjkBZZt6lKZbis","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_cc406a608013437e888cfcd7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/mcp-figma/feature_catalog/08--optional-mcp/optional-mcp-context.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/mcp-figma/feature_catalog/08--optional-mcp/optional-mcp-context.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Optional MCP context\"\n3: description: \"Pull design context FROM Figma as model input through the community Framelink figma manual in this repo's Code Mode; opt-in, discovery-first, and never the official Dev Mode MCP.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"figma mcp\"\n6:   - \"framelink figma mcp\"\n7:   - \"figma code mode\"\n8:   - \"figma_FIGMA_API_KEY\"\n9:   - \"pull figma design context\"\n10: ---\n11: \n12: # Optional MCP context (Code Mode figma.figma_<tool>)\n13: \n14: <!-- sk-doc-template: skill_asset_feature_catalog -->\n15: \n16: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n17: \n18: The skill works fully with the CLI alone. When the agent must pull design context FROM Figma as model input, this opt-in path uses the community Framelink `figma-developer-mcp` manual, already registered as `figma` in this repo's Code Mode (`.utcp_config.json`, stdio). The CLI is the primary surface; the MCP is opt-in.\n19: \n20: The caller reaches this path only when CLI inspection is not enough and design data must enter the model as context. It is READ-ONLY. The boundary to hold: the OFFICIAL Figma Dev Mode MCP is out of scope for this release and is not a supported path — it is mentioned at most as a future option, never promoted. Note that `figma-ds-cli` itself does not ship or spawn its own MCP (source-verified zero hits); its daemon is a private HTTP/WebSocket bridge, not an MCP server.\n21: \n22: ---\n23: \n24: ## 2. HOW IT WORKS\n25: \n26: The Framelink `figma` manual needs a Figma personal token in `.env` as `figma_FIGMA_API_KEY` (Code Mode prefixes the manual name). Calls go through `call_tool_chain()` with the naming `figma.figma_<tool>`. The agent always discovers first with `search_tools()` / `tool_info()` before invoking, and never claims a tool works until discovery confirms it. Live-confirmed tools are `get_figma_data` and `download_figma_images` (reached as `figma.figma_get_figma_data` and `figma.figma_download_figma_images`). Discovering the manual and confirming a concrete tool name and schema is the read-only first step; pulling design context with a confirmed tool is the opt-in read action.\n27: \n28: ---\n29: \n30: ## 3. SOURCE FILES\n31: \n32: ### Implementation\n33: \n34: | File | Layer | Role |\n35: |---|---|---|\n36: | `references/mcp_wiring.md` | Shared | Code Mode `figma` manual wiring, `.env` token, and `figma.figma_<tool>` naming |\n37: | `scripts/print-utcp-snippets.sh` | Script | Prints the Code Mode `.utcp_config.json` snippet for the `figma` manual |\n38: \n39: ### Validation And Tests\n40: \n41: | File | Type | Role |\n42: |---|---|---|\n43: | `manual_testing_playbook/05--optional-mcp/framelink-discovery.md` | Manual playbook | Discovers the `figma` manual and tool names live before any invocation |\n44: \n45: ---\n46: \n47: ## 4. SOURCE METADATA\n48: \n49: - Group: Optional MCP Context\n50: - Canonical catalog source: `feature_catalog.md`\n51: - Feature file path: `08--optional-mcp/optional-mcp-context.md`\n52: \n53: Related references:\n54: - [connect-and-daemon.md](../01--connect-and-daemon/connect-and-daemon.md) covers the primary CLI transport this path is an optional alternative to\n55: - [inspect.md](../02--inspect/inspect.md) covers the CLI read-only inspect verbs that cover most read needs\n\n(End of file - total 55 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Optional MCP context\"\ndescription: \"Pull design context FROM Figma as model input through the community Framelink figma manual in this repo's Code Mode; opt-in, discovery-first, and never the official Dev Mode MCP.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"figma mcp\"\n  - \"framelink figma mcp\"\n  - \"figma code mode\"\n  - \"figma_FIGMA_API_KEY\"\n  - \"pull figma design context\"\n---\n\n# Optional MCP context (Code Mode figma.figma_<tool>)\n\n<!-- sk-doc-template: skill_asset_feature_catalog -->\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nThe skill works fully with the CLI alone. When the agent must pull design context FROM Figma as model input, this opt-in path uses the community Framelink `figma-developer-mcp` manual, already registered as `figma` in this repo's Code Mode (`.utcp_config.json`, stdio). The CLI is the primary surface; the MCP is opt-in.\n\nThe caller reaches this path only when CLI inspection is not enough and design data must enter the model as context. It is READ-ONLY. The boundary to hold: the OFFICIAL Figma Dev Mode MCP is out of scope for this release and is not a supported path — it is mentioned at most as a future option, never promoted. Note that `figma-ds-cli` itself does not ship or spawn its own MCP (source-verified zero hits); its daemon is a private HTTP/WebSocket bridge, not an MCP server.","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/mcp-figma/feature_catalog/08--optional-mcp/optional-mcp-context.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"Optional MCP context\"\ndescription: \"Pull design context FROM Figma as model input through the community Framelink figma manual in this repo's Code Mode; opt-in, discovery-first, and never the official Dev Mode MCP.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"figma mcp\"\n  - \"framelink figma mcp\"\n  - \"figma code mode\"\n  - \"figma_FIGMA_API_KEY\"\n  - \"pull figma design context\"\n---\n\n# Optional MCP context (Code Mode figma.figma_<tool>)\n\n<!-- sk-doc-template: skill_asset_feature_catalog -->\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nThe skill works fully with the CLI alone. When the agent must pull design context FROM Figma as model input, this opt-in path uses the community Framelink `figma-developer-mcp` manual, already registered as `figma` in this repo's Code Mode (`.utcp_config.json`, stdio). The CLI is the primary surface; the MCP is opt-in.\n\nThe caller reaches this path only when CLI inspection is not enough and design data must enter the model as context. It is READ-ONLY. The boundary to hold: the OFFICIAL Figma Dev Mode MCP is out of scope for this release and is not a supported path — it is mentioned at most as a future option, never promoted. Note that `figma-ds-cli` itself does not ship or spawn its own MCP (source-verified zero hits); its daemon is a private HTTP/WebSocket bridge, not an MCP server.\n\n---\n\n## 2. HOW IT WORKS\n\nThe Framelink `figma` manual needs a Figma personal token in `.env` as `figma_FIGMA_API_KEY` (Code Mode prefixes the manual name). Calls go through `call_tool_chain()` with the naming `figma.figma_<tool>`. The agent always discovers first with `search_tools()` / `tool_info()` before invoking, and never claims a tool works until discovery confirms it. Live-confirmed tools are `get_figma_data` and `download_figma_images` (reached as `figma.figma_get_figma_data` and `figma.figma_download_figma_images`). Discovering the manual and confirming a concrete tool name and schema is the read-only first step; pulling design context with a confirmed tool is the opt-in read action.\n\n---\n\n## 3. SOURCE FILES\n\n### Implementation\n\n| File | Layer | Role |\n|---|---|---|\n| `references/mcp_wiring.md` | Shared | Code Mode `figma` manual wiring, `.env` token, and `figma.figma_<tool>` naming |\n| `scripts/print-utcp-snippets.sh` | Script | Prints the Code Mode `.utcp_config.json` snippet for the `figma` manual |\n\n### Validation And Tests\n\n| File | Type | Role |\n|---|---|---|\n| `manual_testing_playbook/05--optional-mcp/framelink-discovery.md` | Manual playbook | Discovers the `figma` manual and tool names live before any invocation |\n\n---\n\n## 4. SOURCE METADATA\n\n- Group: Optional MCP Context\n- Canonical catalog source: `feature_catalog.md`\n- Feature file path: `08--optional-mcp/optional-mcp-context.md`\n\nRelated references:\n- [connect-and-daemon.md](../01--connect-and-daemon/connect-and-daemon.md) covers the primary CLI transport this path is an optional alternative to\n- [inspect.md](../02--inspect/inspect.md) covers the CLI read-only inspect verbs that cover most read needs","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":55,"totalLines":55,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/feature_catalog/08--optional-mcp/optional-mcp-context.md","time":{"start":1781459415890,"end":1781459415894}},"id":"prt_ec7417350001cDpsLLUbJX9P73","sessionID":"ses_138c2bb01ffeUjkBZZt6lKZbis","messageID":"msg_ec7416065001x7c4oH0cPXxdQR"}}
